shortDescription: Binge on movies and TV episodes, news, sports, music and more! We insisted on 720p High Definition for this 24” LED TV, bringing out more lifelike color, texture and detail. We also partnered with Roku to bring you the best possible content with thousands of channels to choose from, conveniently presented through your own customizable home screen. Watch via cable, satellite, HDTV antenna or just start streaming from your favorite app. Like the sound of your own voice You can actually use it with the Roku mobile app to search for the title, artist, actor or director, or just go old-school with our handy remote. We handle all software updates too, automatically, so all you have to worry about is what to watch. Lose yourself in the ultimate viewing experience. Watch onn. with our onn. 24” Class 720P HD LED Roku Smart TV. We're onn. to something here. Say goodbye to stressful decision-making and fear of the electronics aisle. Our mission is simple…to deliver great products and make it easy. Choose onn. and get back to using your brainpower for the important things in life like pondering the question, "What should I binge watch this weekend?"

This Smart TV makes it very easy to watch all the tv and movies you want! Setup is very easy. Once you turn on the power, it guides you step by step right through the entire setup, including a software update. You do need to set up a Roku account from your tablet, phone or computer, but it is free. You even have the option to skip the credit card section for paid streaming services if you prefer. It plays a quick "how to" video to explain how to use the tv and remote and make your way through the menu and all it's options. Adding additional channels is very quick and easy. You will need to get an indoor antenna if you watch over the air free antenna channels like I do, but they are very inexpensive. There are a lot of free streaming movies and shows which is nice should you prefer not to use a paid streaming service, it's still a great tv. The picture quality is very good with nice vibrant colors. It has a nice, sharp picture clarity and great sound quality. The only problem I had was with one free streaming channel buffering, but it ended up being just that channel, as the others were nice and clean. The tv has 3 HDMI inputs to easily connect your other devices, making it a complete entertainment setup. It comes with sturdy legs, but you also have the option to mount to a wall support bracket, which is not included. The Roku stays connected to the internet very well. I did not have any issues with skipping or disconnecting. I highly recommend this tv to others who have a small budget. TV family!"}], 'syndicationSource': None}, {'reviewId': '227043918', 'rating': 5, 'reviewSubmissionTime': '4/11/2020', 'reviewText': 'The setup process was very easy, and the only tool you will need is a Phillips screwdriver to install the two leg stands that are included. Next, make sure you have either a computer, cell phone, or any other device that has an Internet connection so that you can register the product and also sign up for a Roku account or use your existing one.

Similar to an onn. 50 inch 4K version that I own, the screen menus were well organized and easy to navigate through. The picture quality and other settings has a large selection of choices and/or adjustments to fine tune things to your liking, and I was pleasantly surprised to discover that a TV this size contains a "Game mode" in the settings too. Since I am a gamer, this is a welcome feature to have.

In addition to the AV and Antenna TV input sources it also has three different HDMI connections -- one of which has ARC capabilities. What impresses me most about the HDMI ports is that each of them can be customized for different picture quality settings. I find this to be especially useful when I need to use my gaming laptop for 'game mode' only without disturbing the other settings that are appropriate for movies or other presets.

For the most part, the overall picture quality is crisp and vibrant. The streaming movie content looked very good for a TV of this class. My games played smoothly and I didn't experience any lag. The response time was more than adequate. For maximum clarity I find that viewing the TV screen from a distance of about six feet is optimal. The onboard speakers are clear and distortion free, while the headphones delivered exceptional sound output.

The size of the TV itself is well suited for kitchens, university dorms, bathrooms, and other areas with limited space. By it being very lightweight (just over 4 pounds) and portable, it makes for an excellent alternative "monitor" to my laptop's small screen (by way of HDMI connection) as well.

In terms of power consumption, I was informed by customer support that the TV uses approximately "30-40 Watts for 5-6 hours a day." I also want to mention that my experience with onn's customer support team was top-notch and very professional. They were courteous and knowledgeable and answered all my questions satisfactorily.

I'm impressed with the performance of the onn. 24inch 720P HD LED Roku Smart TV: It really surprised me. I have no cable in my bedroom or sewing room and this is a very cool TV to have in a room that only has internet service. 

First it is extremely easy to set up. I actually had it in front of my other TV while doing it. It ran through a list of likes and dislikes to know what content I prefer. Super cool! It requires no extra plugs if you have wireless internet service. When i was setting it up, the TV searched for a wireless service and found mine right away. I merely had to enter my password and off it went downloading content. You do need to set up a Roku account on a separate device such as a smart phone or computer. There is no credit card or payments necessary. There is loads of free content to view. I was able to customize my screen to include content that I prefer to watch. This is all done with the TV remote.

Next viewing is extremely easy as well. I watched 2 different free movies on the first day while in my sewing room. Both came in clear without any lag time. You can pause the content or shut off the TV and resume where you left off earlier. You can not skip commercials. The picture and sound quality are very good for a small TV.

You can set this up to take regular cable. I don't have that in my upper rooms. But there is plenty to watch without it. I love that if i get sick and have to use another room, I will have a TV to watch in bed. If I have company they will have a quality TV to watch.

We appreciate it!'}], 'syndicationSource': None}, {'reviewId': '226945372', 'rating': 5, 'reviewSubmissionTime': '4/9/2020', 'reviewText': 'The 24 class 720P ONN Roku smart TV has a lot of great features! We love that all of the channel options are easy to locate and use (no need to change TV inputs) which is much easier to navigate for older and really young users. Our elderly parents sometimes get confused with changing TV inputs to get to their viewing options and the ONN Roku Smart TV eliminates that extra step. It comes with a standard ROKU remote (see picture) which is about 1 1/2" by 5 1/2". I also like that there are control buttons (see picture) on the side so the TV is still operable if the remote is misplaced. The kids love that it has games included even though you have to watch many ads before they can start to play (one game had 9 ads!!!). The picture is bright and clear and the overall look of the TV is modern and sleek.
 A few things to point out that are lacking in this TV are that it is only 720P but we can expect that for the price. A 1080p model costs more. The remote signal is infrared, not RF, which means it has to be pointed directly at the TV in order to work. This was not an issue for us as this TV is used primarily by our boys and there is a short distance between their seats and the TV itself. The last thing is that the quality of the speakers is not good for low tones. We just used an old pair of speakers we picked up at a resell store and plugged them into the headphone jack and they worked great. I did notice an optical input that would have allowed us a soundbar as well if we had had one.
 Despite this, we feel that this is a good TV for the price! We are more confident having this in our boys room because if it gets accidentally bumped we are not out a lot of money and it works great for them. I would recommend this to someone else with a similar need.', 'reviewTitle': 'Good TV for the price', 'negativeFeedback': 7, 'positiveFeedback': 30, 'userNickname': 'September', 'photos': [{'caption': None, 'id': '7699b1fa-9f50-40c0-8f97-03909ff60ea2', 'sizes': {'normal': {'id': 'normal', 'url': 'https://i5.walmartimages.com/dfw/6e29e393-9bd3/k2-_eddbf8ea-dcce-49b7-b342-2f44d3de11fd.v1.jpg'}, 'thumbnail': {'id': 'thumbnail', 'url': 'https://i5.walmartimages.com/dfw/6e29e393-9bd3/k2-_eddbf8ea-dcce-49b7-b342-2f44d3de11fd.v1.jpg?odnWidth=150&odnHeight=150&odnBg=ffffff'}}}, {'caption': None, 'id': '171751a6-aa00-437e-8b1a-e64e643e8272', 'sizes': {'normal': {'id': 'normal', 'url': 'https://i5.walmartimages.com/dfw/6e29e393-f503/k2-_cfc4773a-9926-446f-90ef-d68ae50092aa.v1.jpg'}, 'thumbnail': {'id': 'thumbnail', 'url': 'https://i5.walmartimages.com/dfw/6e29e393-f503/k2-_cfc4773a-9926-446f-90ef-d68ae50092aa.v1.jpg?odnWidth=150&odnHeight=150&odnBg=ffffff'}}}], 'badges': [{'badgeType': 'Custom', 'id': 'IncentivizedReviewYes', 'contentType': 'REVIEW', 'glassBadge': {'id': 'IncentivizedReview', 'text': 'Incentivized Review'}}, {'badgeType': 'Custom', 'id': 'SRIncentivizedReviewYes', 'contentType': 'REVIEW', 'glassBadge': {'id': 'IncentivizedReview', 'text': 'Incentivized Review'}}], 'clientResponses': [{'date': None, 'department': None, 'logoImage': None, 'name': None, 'response': '

shortDescription: Escape into a world of splendid color and clarity with the X322BV-SR. Clear QAM tuner is included to make cable connection as easy as possible, without an antenna. HDMI input delivers the unbeatable combination of high-definition video and clear audio. A USB port comes in handy when you want to flip through all of your stored pictures and tune into your stored music. More possibilities: with HDMI, VGA, Component and Composite inputs, we offer a convenient balance between the old and new to suit your diverse preferences. With the ability to connect your computer, laptop, monitor, or TV to all your favorite variety of input options, VGA inputs deliver superb analog video.
name: Sceptre 32" Class 720P HD LED TV X322BV-SR

shortDescription: Versatility and performance collide with the new VIZIO D-Series HD Smart TV. D-Series comes loaded with a full array backlight for better contrast and uniformity, brilliant 720p HD resolution and an ultra-fast VIZIO IQ processor with support for immersive audio pass-through for Dolby Atmos and DTS:X. Stream it all with the award-winning SmartCast platform loaded with the best selection of built-in apps including WatchFree+ that lets you enjoy free access to live TV and hundreds of free channels right out of the box. SmartCast also works with Apple AirPlay 2 and Chromecast built-in, offering unparalleled entertainment in a size that fits your lifestyle.
name: VIZIO 24" Class D-Series HD LED Smart TV D24h-J09

shortDescription: Binge on movies and TV episodes, news, sports, music and more! We insisted on 720P High Definition for this 32” LED TV, bringing out more lifelike color, texture and detail. We also partnered with Roku to bring you the best possible content with thousands of channels to choose from, conveniently presented through your own customizable home screen. Watch via cable, satellite, HDTV antenna or just start streaming from your favorite app. Like the sound of your own voice? You can actually use it with the Roku mobile app to search for the title, artist, actor or director, or just go old-school with our handy remote. We handle all software updates too, automatically, so all you have to worry about is what to watch. Lose yourself in the ultimate viewing experience. We're onn.™ to something here. Say goodbye to stressful decision-making and fear of the electronics aisle. Our mission is simple…to deliver great products and make it easy. Choose onn. and get back to using your brainpower for the important things in life like pondering the question, ”What should I binge watch this weekend?”
name: onn. 32” Class HD (720P) LED Roku Smart TV (100012589)

shortDescription: Deck out your entertainment room or even your bedroom with this Philips 32" Class HD (720P) Smart Roku Borderless TV (32PFL6452/F7). Roku TV makes streaming a snap, so you'll always have your favorite show at your fingertips. Philips Roku TV brings you top channels like Netflix, Hulu, YouTube, Google Play, and more. Access to 500,000+ movies and TV episodes across thousands of free or paid channels plus innovative features make finding your favorite entertainment fast and simple. It also has a built-in digital tuner so you can watch digital broadcasts when you're not streaming content.
name: Philips 32" Class HD (720P) Smart Roku Borderless LED TV (32PFL6452/F7)

shortDescription: The 3-Series TCL Roku TV puts all your entertainment favorites in one place, allowing seamless access to over 500,000 movies and TV episodes, your cable box, gaming console, and other devices—all from your simple, intuitive interface. The super-simple remote and dual-band wireless make it fast and easy to access your favorite content in high definition. Connect all your favorite devices with the three HDMI inputs. The built-in TV tuner makes this the ultimate cord-cutting TV as it also gives you the ability to access free, over-the-air HD content.
name: TCL 32" Class 720P HD LED Roku Smart TV 3 Series 32S331

shortDescription: Versatility and performance collide with the VIZIO D-Series HD Smart TV. D-Series comes loaded with a full array backlight for better contrast and uniformity, brilliant 720p HD resolution and an ultra-fast VIZIO IQ processor with support for immersive audio pass-through for Dolby Atmos and DTS:X. Stream it all with the award-winning SmartCast platform loaded with the best selection of built-in apps including WatchFree+ that lets you enjoy free access to live TV and hundreds of free channels right out of the box. SmartCast also works with Apple AirPlay 2 and Chromecast built-in, offering unparalleled entertainment in a size that fits your lifestyle.
name: VIZIO 32" Class D-Series HD Smart TV D32h-J09

[{'reviewId': '261324322', 'rating': 5, 'reviewSubmissionTime': '5/24/2021', 'reviewText': 'I was very excited to give this Vizio 32 inch smart TV a try. I had considered a TV for my bedroom for many years. This Vizio TV has been a very welcomed addition. Setup was super easy and quick. The TV walks you through what needs to be done. This TV was very easy to mount to the wall using a mounting bracket (purchased separately). The TV and remote are an excellent quality. The picture quality is great. The sound is good for coming straight from the TV. I mainly use this TV to watch Netflix, with occasional Disney+ and Prime Video. How nice that these ALL have a button on the remote to link me directly to those apps. I am easily intimidated by technology. But this TV makes everything so easy! I absolutely love it. The one thing that I was disappointed to discover is that the HBO Max app is not yet available. Hopefully that will be available in the future. I also appreciate all of the Watch Free+ channels, which also has a button on the remote to directly take you to that area. There is something to please everyone. Overall, this TV is a great choice. reviews.topNegativeReview.reviewText: So I bought this tv June 2021 and right off the bat the speakers started to distort. Because I ordered on Walmart.com the store wouldn't change it out. The processor speed is annoyingly slow. Now June of 2022 I turned it on only to find the black in the picture is replaced with all red color. On a positive note, when you dial in the picture it is a pretty nice picture.
reviews.topPositiveReview.reviewText:
Very light 32” Vizio Smart TV, each leg takes 2 screws to stand, easy set up, update took about 5 minutes before I could watch my first free movie. 
Picture clear, great sound, SmartCast takes from 5 to 10 seconds to load with so many apps, free TV and free movies, kids shows, etc. Remote has accessible buttons like CC, talk back, and apps like Netflix, Disney+, tubi, prime video. It has Many other features like airplay and cast to share content from IOS devices, amazon Alexa, google assistant, backdrop slideshow, etc. 
With 2 HDMI and 1 USB it's perfect for kids to play games. We all love it. I'm looking into buying a bigger Vizio for the master room.
reviews.topPositiveReview.reviewTitle: Great size for kids or guest room

shortDescription:
For binge-watchers on a budget, be sure to call your spot on the couch. The H4030F3 is born ready with the built-in Roku TV platform, your private portal to more than 5,000 channels and 500,000 movies and TV episodes. So, no matter how many people you have in your house, there are more than enough must-sees and OMGs to go around. Plus, to make the decision even easier, we made the H4030F3 even simpler. It packed with built-in Wi-Fi and faster search. Just connect to the Internet, activate and find your favorite show. With a rich picture and smart features made so easily attainable, it's hard not to love the H4030F3.

Roku OS: Entertain Your Options You can enjoy easy access to 5,000+ channels and 500,000  movies and TV episodes a with Roku TV. But endless  streaming is only the beginning. An intuitive interface and  simplified remote help you get the most out of your current  cable or satellite subscription. Or, cut the cord altogether while  still catching live news, sports and more in striking high  resolution. Whatever your setup, the H4030F3 Roku TV makes  every day a great day to experience the entertainment you love  and discover must-see shows.

Motion Rate: Eyes on the Prize Blinked and you missed it? Think again. The H4030F3 is built  with motion in mind. Motion Rate image processing makes it  so you can keep your eye on the ball, chase scene, or multi-  player battle. Gamers see lag times drop and viewers see all  the key moments in live sports or action movies. Captivating  scenes grab your attention and keep it with smooth motion.

Game Mode: Game On Game Mode offers super-low latency that reduces input lag, so  signals travel faster from your fingers to movement on screen.  Fast responses to each button press make sure the action in  video games is processed quickly and you finish at the top of  the leaderboard.

Fast & Easy Search: A Search Party

Enjoy fast and easy Universal Search that discovers content far  and wide, then displays it all in one place. Simply name a title,  actor or director to find movies and shows featuring their work.  That's all the H4030F3 needs to tell you which items are free or  premium, then point you to where to watch including on-demand  or live TV. It's just as fun as it sounds
name: Hisense 32" Class 720P HD LED LCD Roku Smart TV H4030F Series 32H4030F3

reviews.topPositiveReview.reviewText: Love this TV.  Easy to install and set up.  I use an antenna and have so many channels and viewing options now.  I think the manufacturer should improve upon the remote, however.  There is no way to enter the channel I'd like, I have to scroll through the channels to select. Also, the volume and mute buttons are on the side of the remote and I almost always press them accidentally since they are in the same area as the channel scroll buttons.
reviews.topPositiveReview.reviewTitle: Remote needs improvement, but the tv is great.

shortDescription: This 32" HD RCA ROKU Smart TV delivers a user-friendly experience. The super-simple remote and dual-band wireless make it fast and easy to access your favorite content. This 32" 720p 60Hz LED HDTV has three HDMI inputs for connecting your DVD, Blu Ray player or preferred video game console. Get content from your smartphone or tablet with the free mobile app. This RCA ROKU LED HDTV features a sleek modern design with its quad-pedestal stand. It enhances any room in the house. Roku Search allows you to easily search across top streaming channels by title, actor or director and now includes voice search. With a true 16:9 aspect ratio for viewing your movies the way that the director intended. Catch your favorite broadcast shows in high definition where available. Mount the unit on your wall or set it on top of your entertainment center. RCA + Roku TV puts your favorite broadcast TV programs, streaming channels, gaming console and other devices on an easy to access menu with a super simple remote control. The newly designed remote only has 17 buttons no longer do you need to flip through inputs or complicated menus. Imagine how easy it will be to watch any device, channel or streaming channels RCA + Roku TV is a new era of smart TV. In addition, easily search the top streaming channels like Netflix, Hulu Plus, YouTube, etc. by title, actor or director and find what you want to watch quickly.
name: RCA 32" Class HD 720P Roku Smart LED Television, RTR3260-W, Black

shortDescription: High-definition picture quality in an LG HD TV. Enjoy your favorite scenes even more. HD 720p displays a crisp, clear picture that brings color to your shows and movies. The hard-working quad-core TV processor improves images, action and color, reducing distracting video noise and motion blur, enhancing sharpness and portraying accurate colors. Higher transfer speeds from source to screen with two HDMI inputs for high-performance entertainment. One cable connects audio and video devices quickly and easily. Active HDR enhances your favorite scenes. Discover every detail with scene-by-scene picture adjustment. LG's advanced tone mapping technology makes Active HDR possible, with support for HDR10 and HLG formats.
name: LG 32" Class HD (720p) Smart LED TV (32LM577BZUA)

shortDescription: Versatility and performance collide with the new D-Series FHD Smart TV that comes loaded with a full array backlight for better contrast and uniformity, brilliant 1080p Full HD resolution and an ultra-fast VIZIO IQ processor with support for immersive audio pass-through for Dolby Atmos and DTS:X. Game on with the V-Gaming Engine that enables next-level gaming performance with features like Variable Refresh Rate with AMD FreeSync, auto game mode, low-latency gaming, and newly added gaming menu. D-Series blends power, speed and versatile size. Stream it all with the award-winning SmartCast platform loaded with the best selection of built-in apps including WatchFree+ that lets you enjoy free access to live TV and hundreds of free channels right out of the box. SmartCast also works with Apple AirPlay 2 and Chromecast built-in, offering unparalleled entertainment in a size that fits your lifestyle.
name: VIZIO 24" Class D-Series FHD LED Smart TV D24f-J09

reviews.topNegativeReview.reviewText: I bought this TV in January, used it minimally (mostly to listen to pandora). Had to factory reset it a few weeks ago because it kept freezing up. shortDescription: The 3-Series TCL Roku TV puts all your entertainment favorites in one place, allowing seamless access to over 500,000movies and TV episodes, your cable box, gaming console, and other devices, all from our simple, intuitive Roku interface. The super-simple remote and dual-band wireless make it fast and easy to access your favorite content in high definition. Connect all your favorite devices with the three HDMI inputs. The built-in TV tuner makes this the ultimate cord-cutting TV as it also gives you the ability to access free, over-the-air HD content.
name: TCL 32" Class 1080P FHD LED Roku Smart TV 3 Series 32S327

[{'reviewId': '287883816', 'rating': 5, 'reviewSubmissionTime': '10/10/2022', 'reviewText': "Very easy set up. Walks you thru step by step.  Word of advice. Before you set up your TV,  SET UP a  ROKU ACCOUNT online. It's free. Remember your login and password. When you set up the TV, it will find you and you can skip that step.  ALSO, THERE IS NO CHARGE for a ROKU ACCOUNT… but when you set it up, it wants you to SUBSCRIBE TO ROKU TV… SKIP IT BY SCROLLING DOWN TO THE BOTTOM TO THE PAGE AND “SKIP” .     
The picture is great on the 1080,  I bought the TCL/ROKU WIRELESS SPEAKER. No HDMI OR OPTICAL CABLES TO HOOK UP OR PURCHASE.  This feature saves you one of the 3 HDMI ports this TV HAS, one of which is ARC capable.  
The TCL/ ROKU 32” SPEAKER just plugs the into your wall outlet, and the TV finds it and you get great sound. It Uses your WIFI.   It's also wall mountable and includes the mounting hardware.   You need to,pay careful attention to the size of an external speaker as the TV sits low and a speaker MAY BLOCK THE RF REMOTE SIGNAL GETTING TO THE TV.  You may need to raise up the TV off the table, mount theTV to a wall, or mount the Speaker to a wall. 
If you don't want the TV's RF LED white standby light to stay illuminated when the TV turns off, go to HOME> scroll down to SETTINGS> then over to SYSTEM>over to POWER>over to STANDBY LED> and SELECT OFF. 
The TV also found my BluRay player when hooked up via HDMI.  
I added a Amazon FIRE STICK and it set up without a problem.  
ROKU also has the SPECTRUM TV app, so I'm able to watch every Spectrum channel I subscribe to.   
HINT Owners of IPad or iPhones can UTILIZE APPLE AIR PLAY ON THIS TV AND YOUR DEVICE TO SCROLL THRU SPECTRUM CHANNELS AND USE IT AS A REMOTE.  Saves time since this TV DOES NOT HAVE A REMOTE WITH A NUMBER PAD.  Download the Spectrum TV GUIDE APP,  set up AIR PLAY  on the TV and Device, and you can use the Spectrum's TV GUIDE  to scroll thru the channels, select one and it appears on the TV. 
Overall I'm glad I bought this TV and was impressed with the ease of set up and functionalit.", 'reviewTitle': None, 'negativeFeedback': 0, 'positiveFeedback': 0, 'userNickname': 'Lee', 'photos': [{'caption': None, 'id': 'b8f34a02-053b-4aef-adbd-e7c6d4338d49', 'sizes': {'normal': {'id': 'normal', 'url': 'https://i5.walmartimages.com/dfw/6e29e393-d8d1/k2-_bd122b26-de72-4cdd-a936-b1eb3f3d0c9d.v1.bin'}, 'thumbnail': {'id': 'thumbnail', 'url': 'https://i5.walmartimages.com/dfw/6e29e393-d8d1/k2-_bd122b26-de72-4cdd-a936-b1eb3f3d0c9d.v1.bin?odnWidth=150&odnHeight=150&odnBg=ffffff'}}}, {'caption': None, 'id': '2d01171d-86eb-44cc-8702-699749a32b25', 'sizes': {'normal': {'id': 'normal', 'url': 'https://i5.walmartimages.com/dfw/6e29e393-8aff/k2-_79bedc93-e7b0-4a4c-bf12-0647c89c6ffb.v1.bin'}, 'thumbnail': {'id': 'thumbnail', 'url': 'https://i5.walmartimages.com/dfw/6e29e393-8aff/k2-_79bedc93-e7b0-4a4c-bf12-0647c89c6ffb.v1.bin?odnWidth=150&odnHeight=150&odnBg=ffffff'}}}], 'badges': [{'badgeType': 'Custom', 'id': 'VerifiedPurchaser', 'contentType': 'REVIEW', 'glassBadge': {'id': 'VerifiedPurchaser', 'text': 'Verified Purchaser'}}], 'clientResponses': None, 'syndicationSource': None}, {'reviewId': '286036630', 'rating': 5, 'reviewSubmissionTime': '9/13/2022', 'reviewText': 'We went to an AirBnB that had a RokuTV, and I was intrigued. I gotta say, I am VERY impressed with how easy it was to set up this TV! But that being said, it did help that I already had another Roku device in the house, so it just transferred all my apps and settings over to this TV. It's very hard to find a 32" TV with 1080p, so that was a big plus in buying this one -- the image quality is excellent. If you're going to get a sound bar to go with this TV, make sure it is HDMI-ARC compatible, so this TV will sync with the sound bar and you won't need to use a separate remote to control it. Works great with my Sony BluRay player (using HDMI) as well. A BIG plus for me on this TV is the over-the-air Digital TV tuner -- it shows a full complete channel guide of the over-the-air antenna broadcast shows that are available. I was STUNNED by this -- I've NEVER had a digital TV take the channel guide to this level of detail! The other nice thing is that if you need to change input sources on your TV, it is done graphically rather than with a bunch of tedious buttons on your remote. You also have the ability to change the input name from (in my case) HDMI 1 to Blu Ray Player (press the * button when the input name is higlighted), so you don't need to guess what device is on that input. All in all, a very well thought-out TV. The ONLY complaint I have is with the Roku remote -- I wish that small little thing had the ability to control the functions on my Blu Ray player -- so I still have to use the manufacturer remote for that. reviews.topPositiveReview.reviewText:
Very easy set up. Walks you thru step by step.  Word of advice. Before you set up your TV,  SET UP a  ROKU ACCOUNT online. It's free. Remember your login and password. When you set up the TV, it will find you and you can skip that step.  ALSO, THERE IS NO CHARGE for a ROKU ACCOUNT… but when you set it up, it wants you to SUBSCRIBE TO ROKU TV… SKIP IT BY SCROLLING DOWN TO THE BOTTOM TO THE PAGE AND “SKIP” .     
The picture is great on the 1080,  I bought the TCL/ROKU WIRELESS SPEAKER. No HDMI OR OPTICAL CABLES TO HOOK UP OR PURCHASE.  This feature saves you one of the 3 HDMI ports this TV HAS, one of which is ARC capable.  
The TCL/ ROKU 32” SPEAKER just plugs the into your wall outlet, and the TV finds it and you get great sound. It Uses your WIFI.   It's also wall mountable and includes the mounting hardware.   You need to,pay careful attention to the size of an external speaker as the TV sits low and a speaker MAY BLOCK THE RF REMOTE SIGNAL GETTING TO THE TV.  You may need to raise up the TV off the table, mount theTV to a wall, or mount the Speaker to a wall. 
If you don't want the TV's RF LED white standby light to stay illuminated when the TV turns off, go to HOME> scroll down to SETTINGS> then over to SYSTEM>over to POWER>over to STANDBY LED> and SELECT OFF. 
The TV also found my BluRay player when hooked up via HDMI.  
I added a Amazon FIRE STICK and it set up without a problem.  
ROKU also has the SPECTRUM TV app, so I'm able to watch every Spectrum channel I subscribe to.   
HINT Owners of IPad or iPhones can UTILIZE APPLE AIR PLAY ON THIS TV AND YOUR DEVICE TO SCROLL THRU SPECTRUM CHANNELS AND USE IT AS A REMOTE.  Saves time since this TV DOES NOT HAVE A REMOTE WITH A NUMBER PAD.  Download the Spectrum TV GUIDE APP,  set up AIR PLAY  on the TV and Device, and you can use the Spectrum's TV GUIDE  to scroll thru the channels, select one and it appears on the TV. 
Overall I'm glad I bought this TV and was impressed with the ease of set up and functionalit.

shortDescription: Featuring a novel and lightweight design, the Sceptre 43 LED HDTV delivers riveting visuals and excitement beyond your expectations. 1080P Resolution provides exceptional brilliance and clarity in every pixel. With multiple HDMI ports, picture quality and streaming access is available at its fullest potential. Clear QAM conveniently delivers your cable channels without the need for an antenna. View your pictures as a slideshow or listen to your favorite music via the USB port. Just insert your flash drive into the USB port for the ultimate entertainment. Enjoy lifelike pictures complete with bright colors and crisp images with the Sceptre 43 LED HDTV.
name: Sceptre 43" Class 1080P FHD LED TV X435BV-F

reviews.topNegativeReview.reviewText: Ordered this tv the first one the box came wet and tv did not work, the next one now has the lights In the tv flicker and there's a red line down the right side of the tv after a month of use.
reviews.topPositiveReview.reviewText: I originally bought this tv because my old one just gave out. I read all the reviews and was a bit worried about what some were saying we're sound issues. I have not had any problems with the sound on mine. I mean you aren't going to have theater quality sound but who really expects that without a surround sound system any way. I can't even turn this thing up half way and it's to loud for me so for those of you worried about the reviews complaining about the sound. Don't! The picture quality is great the sound is more than enough for a normal room and it's surprisingly light weight and easy to set up. I'm 50 years old and not at all mechanically inclined and it took me less than 15 minutes to do alone. I highly recommend this tv to anyone looking for a new boob tube!

shortDescription: Binge on movies and TV episodes, news, sports, music and more! We insisted on 1080P Full High Definition for this 42” LED TV, bringing out more lifelike color, texture and detail. We also partnered with Roku to bring you the best possible content with thousands of channels to choose from, conveniently presented through your own customizable home screen. Watch via cable, satellite, HDTV antenna or just start streaming from your favorite app. Like the sound of your own voice? You can actually use it with the Roku mobile app to search for the title, artist, actor or director, or just go old-school with our handy remote. We handle all software updates too, automatically, so all you have to worry about is what to watch. Lose yourself in the ultimate viewing experience. We're onn.™ to something here. Say goodbye to stressful decision-making and fear of the electronics aisle. Our mission is simple…to deliver great products and make it easy. Choose onn. and get back to using your brainpower for the important things in life like pondering the question, "What should I binge watch this weekend?"
name: onn. 42” Class FHD (1080P) LED Roku Smart TV (100068372)

reviews.topPositiveReview.reviewText: I love my new 42"Onn tv. Ive only had a week, but will update if anything changes. Easy setup and connect devices. Home button takes you to choose which device you want to use, picture is great, you also have many options for adjustment. Simple and easy to use especially for seniors like me. Dont need to be tech savy. Just press home key and choose your source. I also have 2 Onn 7" tablets. they are a little slow, but they arent 5g so its to be expected, but they work great for games like Hearthstone and other Google play games. I have only had positive experiences with Onn products.

shortDescription: Versatility and performance collide with the new D-Series FHD Smart TV that comes loaded with a full array backlight for better contrast and uniformity, brilliant 1080p Full HD resolution and an ultra-fast VIZIO IQ processor with support for immersive audio pass-through for Dolby Atmos and DTS:X. Game on with the V-Gaming Engine that enables next-level gaming performance with features like Variable Refresh Rate with AMD FreeSync, auto game mode, low-latency gaming, and newly added gaming menu.   D-Series blends power, speed and versatile size. Stream it all with the award-winning SmartCast platform loaded with the best selection of built-in apps including WatchFree+ that lets you enjoy free access to live TV and hundreds of free channels right out of the box. SmartCast also works with Apple AirPlay 2 and Chromecast built-in, offering unparalleled entertainment in a size that fits your lifestyle.
name: VIZIO 24" Class Full HD LED SmartCast Smart TV D-Series D24f4-J01

Even Roku and Fire smart TVs have issues. I want streaming features and I bought a Roku; it's speedy and doesn't crash. Entry level TVs like this one are sold at a loss. Alternative revenue streams is how they get that money back: an ad for a Disney movie at the front of the box offsets the cost. Data mining is the other road that Vizio takes here. The smart features are displayed prominently because they want your information to sell to third parties. I do not connect my TV to the Internet and use antenna and my Roku Express 4K . There are several dead pixels on the right side. Viewing angle is not the best. Speakers are nothing great but I have heard worse. I attached a pair of PC speakers to boost the volume. 
It changes channels quickly and integrates with my Roku well. I want to hide their "smart" features from my input list. I can't.
It worked well when I have my Xbox series S hooked up to it also.
Updates to their proprietary software are going to be less frequent than you get with a separate streaming player. Seems I have read that you cannot add channels to the built in steaming features.
I am happy with it for my use set: over-air TV and my Roku Express 4K  device.
Stay away from hooking this little girl up to the Internet and do not consider using the smart TV features that are built in as they will only cause you pain later down the road.', 'reviewTitle': 'Good TV. reviews.topPositiveReview.reviewText: It took me several minutes to figure out how to get it to work with just my attic antenna.  I have a Roku but didn't want it to connect through that.  After disconnecting the Roku and the internet, I skipped everything until it took me to the tv searching for tv channels (over the air).  After that, I used the input button on the remote to take me to the channels and not Roku or my computer.  Unlike the remote to my Samsung, I can't pull up a menu to show me what's what on the channel selection (yet).  The picture is great and easy to adjust (pic).  The sound quality is far superior to the same size Samsung I had.  While I'm not the brightest elderly bulb in the package, I was actually able to figure this tv out and love it.  For my bedroom it is the perfect size.

shortDescription: Enjoy smart TV functionality in HD with the JVC MAW205 Select Series 32-In.-Class 720p HD Smart LED TV. The Roku TV operating system provides access to a variety of streaming apps and services, such as Netflix, Disney+, and Pandora. The TV uses an LED-backlit LCD panel and sports 3 HDMI inputs for digital HD sources like cable/satellite boxes and gaming consoles. Plus, you can display your JPEG photos from an optional USB drive. A composite video input lets you connect legacy devices, like a VCR. A remote is included as an added convenience.
name: JVC 32" Class HD (720P) Roku Smart LED TV LT-32MAW205

shortDescription: For binge-watchers on a budget, be sure to call your spot on the couch. The H4030F1 is born ready with the built-in Roku TV platform, your private portal to more than 5,000 channels, and 500,000 movies and TV episodes. So, no matter how many people you have in your house, there are more than enough must-sees and OMGs to go around. Plus, to make the decision even easier, we made the H4030F1 even simpler. It is packed with built-in Wi-Fi and faster search. Just connect to the Internet, activate, and find your favorite show. With a rich picture and smart features made so easily attainable, it’s hard not to love the H4030F1.
name: Hisense 40" Class 2K FHD LED LCD Roku Smart TV H4030F Series 40H4030F1

shortDescription: Versatility and performance collide with the new D-Series FHD Smart TV that comes loaded with a full array backlight for better contrast and uniformity, brilliant 1080p Full HD resolution and an ultra-fast VIZIO IQ processor with support for immersive audio pass-through for Dolby Atmos and DTS:X. Game on with the V-Gaming Engine that enables next-level gaming performance with features like Variable Refresh Rate with AMD FreeSync, auto game mode, low-latency gaming, and newly added gaming menu. D-Series blends power, speed and versatile size. Stream it all with the award-winning SmartCast platform loaded with the best selection of built-in apps including WatchFree+ that lets you enjoy free access to live TV and hundreds of free channels right out of the box. SmartCast also works with Apple AirPlay 2 and Chromecast built-in, offering unparalleled entertainment in a size that fits your lifestyle.
name: VIZIO 32" Class D-Series FHD LED Smart TV D32f-J04

reviews.topNegativeReview.reviewText: I purchased this TV in November 2021.  It was easy to set up and used it with my Roku stick and an antenna for local channels.  Then, all of a sudden Vizio did an update of the TV and will only let you use the "Smartcast" version.  From there, I had a host of issues including I couldn't use my Roku at all.  I tried all sorts of Googling, videos, etc. and it would not work.  Also, we use Philo and Philo is not an app Smartcast supports.  Nowhere to add it either as I tried.  For a 68 year old lady, the Smartcast which didn't appear to be an option to remove or revert to the old format is not User friendly in my opinion.  I just want to watch from my Roku, and stream.  I replaced this TV with a non Smart TV and I now have everything I had before with Roku and my local antenna.  This Vizio is going in our annual garage sale.

reviews.topPositiveReview.reviewText: I was pleasantly surprised at the quality of this tv.  It has all the apps you could want.  The picture quality is very good for an inexpensive tv (not cheap).  I bought this primarily to use a monitor, but it works great as a small bedroom tv.  But I was really surprised that I was able to hook up my very old computer/gaming systems (Atari 400 and Apple IIc) to it.  The only drawback might be that the wireless is only n class but I don't notice any lag.  Also, it weighs next to nothing.  I move this around to different rooms and even to my outside deck.  Got a great deal from Walmart.  If you do buy this I hope you have just as much luck with it as I have.
reviews.topPositiveReview.reviewTitle: I would recommend this for any small room.

shortDescription: With a Sceptre 43-inch LED 4K UHD TV (U435CV-U), entertainment is transformed into an epic adventure. The unequalled color and clear brilliance of 4K (3840 x 2160 or over eight million pixels) will provide more natural and lifelike images than have ever been viewed on a 43-inch screen. Multiple HDMI ports allow you to connect up to four devices at once, so you can stream, browse and listen to all of your favorite multimedia. The HDMI ports are equipped with HDMI 2.0, which let you seamlessly stream 4K video to get the most rewarding viewing experience that is available on the market.
name: Sceptre 43" Class 4K UHD LED TV HDR U435CV-U

'rating': 4, 'reviewSubmissionTime': '10/7/2016', 'reviewText': 'Screen reflects a lot of ambient light so is best viewed in darkened room.

I use with antenna, so am not able to source 4k. 1080p works well and is sufficient resolution for TV viewing. 4k would be very useful if screen were being used as a computer monitor at close distance.
There is no audio out that is volume adjustable by the TV. Even what appears as a head set output, in the manual, does not have volume controlled by the TV. I had to buy a separate 3.5mm to two RCA adapter cable to get the audio into my entertainment system, and I have to use the separate entertainment system remote to control the audio volume. It would be nice to use the TV remote to control the volume but that is not possible with this 43" TV.  (Sceptre's 40" TV does offer volume control of the 3.5mm audio output.)

I had to make sure the TV surround sound processor is turned off so it doesn't conflict with the surround sound processor in my entertainment system.

This TV replaced my old 40 inch CRT tube TV. The flat screen feet extend forward from the flat screen over 4 inches, for stability. This forces the screen to be more than 4 inches away from the front edge of the surface supporting the TV.  The old CRT tube used to be right up by the front edge of the cabinet, so I discarded the flat screen's feet, and constructed a stand for the TV using a flat piece of cabinet wood, corner brackets, and aluminum angle. I mounted this flat screen using the wall mount screw holes at the back of the TV, allowing the TV screen to now be as close to the front of my cabinet, as was my old CRT screen. 

The black bezel frame around the screen is very nice. It's only .5 inch wide and 3.3 inch of that is flat and rough textured to not reflect glaring light.

The instructions provided are readable, but do not provide much information. The function of all the connectors is not very detailed. To compensate for this lack of information, however, I found the technical support line to be quick and professional. They explained to me that I had to press "5-1" on the remote to get channel 5, as just pressing "5" will not work. They also explained that the L and R audio output sockets do not work, and the only way to get audio out to RCA connectors, was to purchase a separate adapter cable for use with the 3.5mm output, and that doing that does not provide volume control.

The TV did arrive in perfect condition and on the date promised. It has been working well, with the above mentioned limitations, for a week or so.

shortDescription: The TCL 4-Series Roku TV offers stunning 4K picture quality with four times the resolution of Full HD for enhanced clarity and detail, as well as endless entertainment with thousands of streaming channels. High dynamic range (HDR) technology delivers bright and accurate colors for a lifelike viewing experience. In addition, your favorite HD shows, movies, and sporting events are enhanced to near Ultra HD resolution with 4K Upscaling. Your favorite broadcast TV, streaming channels, gaming console and other devices are front-and-center within a simple, customizable home screen. There’s no more flipping through inputs or wading through complicated menus. The super-simple remote—with about half the number of buttons on a traditional TV remote—puts you in control of your favorite entertainment and includes one-touch shortcuts to popular channels like Netflix.
name: TCL 55" Class 4-Series 4K UHD HDR Smart Roku TV - 55S41

We are using it in our bedroom and love it!', 'reviewTitle': 'TCL Roku 55" TV', 'negativeFeedback': 0, 'positiveFeedback': 0, 'userNickname': 'GeekITProFamily', 'photos': [{'caption': None, 'id': '531d9d02-77ff-4373-ba58-7bcc5d7f4724', 'sizes': {'normal': {'id': 'normal', 'url': 'https://i5.walmartimages.com/dfw/6e29e393-6ded/k2-_04d500dc-5784-48c6-b14d-2b747d07e9a8.v1.bin'}, 'thumbnail': {'id': 'thumbnail', 'url': 'https://i5.walmartimages.com/dfw/6e29e393-6ded/k2-_04d500dc-5784-48c6-b14d-2b747d07e9a8.v1.bin?odnWidth=150&odnHeight=150&odnBg=ffffff'}}}, {'caption': None, 'id': '6f357f66-7cc0-4966-b318-0df8875eea14', 'sizes': {'normal': {'id': 'normal', 'url': 'https://i5.walmartimages.com/dfw/6e29e393-156c/k2-_3cb23abd-0207-4ecc-a6da-a5673bd83f4d.v1.bin'}, 'thumbnail': {'id': 'thumbnail', 'url': 'https://i5.walmartimages.com/dfw/6e29e393-156c/k2-_3cb23abd-0207-4ecc-a6da-a5673bd83f4d.v1.bin?odnWidth=150&odnHeight=150&odnBg=ffffff'}}}], 'badges': [{'badgeType': 'Custom', 'id': 'IncentivizedReviewYes', 'contentType': 'REVIEW', 'glassBadge': {'id': 'IncentivizedReview', 'text': 'Incentivized Review'}}], 'clientResponses': None, 'syndicationSource': None}, {'reviewId': '289030759', 'rating': 5, 'reviewSubmissionTime': '10/24/2022', 'reviewText': 'First off, any review placing this at a 1 star because you received the unit damaged in shipping is asinine. A shipping company mishandling your package has nothing to do with the quality of the TV, nor does it do anything to hamper the shipping company, who are the ones that actually deserve the 1-star review.

For what you get from this television it's hard to find a competitor at this price, full stop. Only one, maybe two other companies make televisions with relative quality and features that are in this class.

I upgraded from a 50" TCL Roku set to this one. The 50" unit I purchased in 2019 had nothing wrong with it, I just wanted something a hair larger for the bedroom and my son needed a replacement for his aging 32". That said, the majority of issues I had with that tv were fixed in this updated model.

With my previous TCL tv my biggest issues were the backlight and the brightness level of HDR content. Of course, at these prices, you can't expect amazingly brilliant performance, but I always found myself not wanting to watch HDR content because the brightness just wasn't there. However, with this newer unit, the performance is much better. I think a lot of that has to do with the fact that this television features a "full panel backlight" (a row of LEDs arranged in a strip across the unit) as opposed to the older one, which utilized edge-lit backlighting (the backlight LEDs sit in rows along the edge). The diffuse material layer also seems to be made of something far more even, as the light level distribution is more evenly distributed. This combined with a better display panel makes for a much more pleasant experience, one where I can be satisfied watching HDR content.

Another thing I was impressed with was the black levels. Generally, on a tv in this class, you get fairly muddy blacks, with light bleed leaking through, but for the most part, the black separation was better than expected. 

The biggest caveat with these TVs is their adjustability vs convenience. For most people the amount of control you have is sufficient. Everything is very straightforward when it comes to setting up the image properties and it will be easy for almost anyone to adjust to their liking. The downside is that there just aren't any power user settings. You can't adjust individual color channel hues or saturations, there are no motion or refresh rate settings (although I see that as a plus, most motion enhancement systems are terrible) and you are generally limited to the basic range of things. That said, you can still get a great image out of it with relative ease.

This really is a great tv for this price range. One last thing, people want to complain about the speakers, but almost any modern tv under a significant price range is going to have dinky little speakers. reviews.topNegativeReview.reviewText: Given a broken tv and employees were not helpful and didn't believe I purchased tv
reviews.topPositiveReview.reviewText: I wall mounted this tv in my game room where kids watch most of the time. The mounting was pretty easieras its smaller and with all the tools it took about 20 minutes. I didn't expect the picture quality to be same as my other branded tv but when I turned it on, the quality was perfect. I also liked the smart tv options but sometimes I am noticing some audio-visual non- sync. Not sure if its because of internet or some other problem but overall this is a good quality smart tv with lots of options. Other thing I liked is the simple remote with a few buttons but lots of options. That makes it user friendly even kids can use it without messing up with options. Its perfect for my game room. Hope it stays the same for long time.

shortDescription: Improve your home viewing experience with the SAMSUNG 32" Class HD 720P Smart LED TV (UN32M4500). It features built-in Wi-Fi, so you can connect to the web and many streaming options. It also has an Ethernet port for a wired connection and HDMI ports for adding gaming consoles and other equipment. This Full HD Smart LED TV displays a high quality picture with Ultra Clean View, PurColor and Micro Dimming Pro technologies. Use mirroring to watch the same show on the TV and on your phone at the same time.
name: SAMSUNG 32" Class HD (720P) Smart LED TV UN32M4500

shortDescription: Versatility and performance collide with the new D-Series FHD Smart TV that comes loaded with a full array backlight for better contrast and uniformity, brilliant 1080p Full HD resolution and an ultra-fast VIZIO IQ processor with support for immersive audio pass-through for Dolby Atmos and DTS:X. Game on with the V-Gaming Engine that enables next-level gaming performance with features like Variable Refresh Rate with AMD FreeSync, auto game mode, low-latency gaming, and newly added gaming menu. D-Series blends power, speed and versatile size. Stream it all with the award-winning SmartCast platform loaded with the best selection of built-in apps including WatchFree+ that lets you enjoy free access to live TV and hundreds of free channels right out of the box. SmartCast also works with Apple AirPlay 2 and Chromecast built-in, offering unparalleled entertainment in a size that fits your lifestyle.
name: VIZIO 40" Class D-Series FHD LED Smart TV D40f-J09

It makes it super easy for anyone to use!", 'reviewTitle': 'Beautiful Picture!', 'negativeFeedback': 0, 'positiveFeedback': 21, 'userNickname': 'sullenriot182', 'photos': [{'caption': None, 'id': 'd47f0cdb-641b-42c0-b352-5cda41a0be27', 'sizes': {'normal': {'id': 'normal', 'url': 'https://i5.walmartimages.com/dfw/6e29e393-de48/k2-_bfe064b1-cfd6-44e3-ba4c-1ada7e5ef48e.v1.bin'}, 'thumbnail': {'id': 'thumbnail', 'url': 'https://i5.walmartimages.com/dfw/6e29e393-de48/k2-_bfe064b1-cfd6-44e3-ba4c-1ada7e5ef48e.v1.bin?odnWidth=150&odnHeight=150&odnBg=ffffff'}}}], 'badges': [{'badgeType': 'Custom', 'id': 'IncentivizedReviewYes', 'contentType': 'REVIEW', 'glassBadge': {'id': 'IncentivizedReview', 'text': 'Incentivized Review'}}], 'clientResponses': None, 'syndicationSource': None}, {'reviewId': '260132516', 'rating': 5, 'reviewSubmissionTime': '5/9/2021', 'reviewText': "This 40 inch Vizio Smart TV is a great investment! It was very easy to set up right out of the box. The two legs screw into the bottom with two screws that are in the package for the remote. The remote comes with two batteries so you can use it immediately. The on-screen set up was quick and easy to follow. The TV connected to our internet as soon as we entered the password. The TV is very light so you can move it or hold it on the wall with no problem. The picture is exactly what you have come to expect from these flat screen tv's..it's great. The colors are sharp. The frame around the outside is thin and does not distract from your viewing. There are two speakers with volume that goes up to 100. We are currently using this with no sound system and are happy with the factory sound. There is an interactive tour and set up guide that you can access online that is easy to refer to and helps you learn about the many settings you have to choose from. reviews.topPositiveReview.reviewText: I plugged this TV in and automatically picked up the internet; then it asked for the internet password, updated, and was ready to go. There are so many channels, and the stations are right on the main menu, so it is effortless to find your favorite show. It doesn't buffer, and the program comes on immediately. The picture is clear, bright, and you can adjust to your liking, and the sound is good for only the tv speakers. The stand was very easy to screw on with included screws. Remote also came with batteries.

shortDescription: For binge-watchers on a budget, be sure to call your spot on the couch. The H4030F1 is born ready with the built-in Roku TV platform, your private portal to more than 5,000 channels, and 500,000 movies and TV episodes. So, no matter how many people you have in your house, there are more than enough must-sees and OMGs to go around. Plus, to make the decision even easier, we made the H4030F1 even simpler. It is packed with built-in Wi-Fi and faster search. Just connect to the Internet, activate, and find your favorite show. With a rich picture and smart features made so easily attainable, it’s hard not to love the H4030F1.
name: Hisense 43" Class 2K FHD LED Roku Smart TV H4030F Series 43H4030F1

Then I put the feet on while it was leaning against something easily. Did not need to lay it flat anywhere which is another risk of something happening. All was easy and pretty fast but took my time. One thing I did not like was getting the tape off of the screen.  I lifted it from the back of the TV easily BUT when it got to the edge where it meets the front of the TV\'s screen it tore off in a straight line almost like it was perforated! Tried the other side and same thing. Leaving me wondering how to get it off the screen itself. I called the makers and a guy there said to use rubbing alcohol slowly a little at a time to get it to start lifting off.  I tried some and was not getting anywhere with that idea. So tried to get it to just start to lift at the bottom of the screen where it ended with just lightly and carefully scrapping the edge in an upward motion.  I had tweezers just in case needed. I did this and carefully got the tape to life just a bit and carefully used the tweezers to just grip the tiny corner that was up and when it started lifting I easily pulled it all up the whole side of the screen! PHEW! Same thing on the other side. DONE! There is also tape on top of the screen but I was extra careful removing it so wanted to see if it was possible without tearing off like both sides did previously. If you lift it up from the back and then when you get to where it meets the screen and slow and carefully lift it up and over the edge then the rest comes off as expected. No need to go through everything I went through. I got this mostly to use with my Wii system. I saw it had the RCA ports on the back that m,any TVs do not have. Worked just as I hoped. It has the video and sound ports that match the Wii perfectly. Also should work with any old component that needs these types of ports before USB etc were invented. My niece said that she needed a converter box for hers to work. Not sure what TV she has. The old TV that I was using in the game room was a 33" SONY CRT TV that I cannot lift by myself and it was acting up. reviews.topPositiveReview.reviewText: Great out of the box. Mounted to the wall plugged in did the setup took about 15 min and little more to signup to ROKU. Has a nice picture and great colors

shortDescription: Binge on movies and TV episodes, news, sports, music and more! We insisted on 4K Ultra High Definition for this 43” LED TV, bringing out more lifelike color, texture and detail. We also partnered with Roku to bring you the best possible content with thousands of channels to choose from, conveniently presented through your own customizable home screen. Watch via cable, satellite, HDTV antenna or just start streaming from your favorite app. Like the sound of your own voice? You can actually use it with the Roku mobile app to search for the title, artist, actor or director, or just go old-school with our handy remote. We handle all software updates too, automatically, so all you have to worry about is what to watch. Lose yourself in the ultimate viewing experience. We're onn.™ to something here. Say goodbye to stressful decision-making and fear of the electronics aisle. Our mission is simple…to deliver great products and make it easy. Choose onn. and get back to using your brainpower for the important things in life like pondering the question, "What should I binge watch this weekend?"
name: onn. 43” Class 4K UHD (2160P) LED Roku Smart TV HDR (100012584)

shortDescription: Binge on movies and TV episodes, news, sports, music and more! We insisted on 720P High Definition for this 39” LED TV, bringing out more lifelike color, texture and detail. We also partnered with Roku to bring you the best possible content with thousands of channels to choose from, conveniently presented through your own customizable home screen. Watch via cable, satellite, HDTV antenna or just start streaming from your favorite app. Like the sound of your own voice? You can actually use it with the Roku mobile app to search for the title, artist, actor or director, or just go old-school with our handy remote. We handle all software updates too, automatically, so all you have to worry about is what to watch. Lose yourself in the ultimate viewing experience. We're onn.™ to something here. Say goodbye to stressful decision-making and fear of the electronics aisle. Our mission is simple…to deliver great products and make it easy. Choose onn. and get back to using your brainpower for the important things in life like pondering the question, "What should I binge watch this weekend?"
name: onn. 39” Class HD (720P) LED Roku Smart TV (100074926)

shortDescription: The 4-Series Roku TV delivers stunning 4K picture quality with four times the resolution of Full HD for enhanced clarity and detail, as well as endless entertainment with thousands of streaming channels. High dynamic range (HDR) technology delivers bright and accurate colors for a lifelike viewing experience. In addition, your favorite HD shows, movies, and sporting events are upscaled to near Ultra HD resolution with 4K Upscaling. The simple, personalized home screen allows seamless access to thousands of streaming channels, plus your cable box, Blu-ray player, gaming console, and other devices without flipping through inputs or complicated menus. The super-simple remote—with about half the number of buttons on a traditional TV remote—puts you in control of your favorite entertainment.
name: TCL 43" Class 4-Series 4K UHD HDR Roku Smart TV - 43S431

shortDescription: Enjoying full HD just got easier. RCA Roku TV puts your favorite broadcast TV programs, streaming channels, gaming console and other devices side-by-side in a simple, intuitive interface. Experience 1080P content with the incredible clarity of FULL HD resolution. The new 1080P RCA ROKU TV allows seamless access to over 500,000 streaming channels such as Netflix, Vudu, and YouTube. This 40" 1080P FHD RCA ROKU Smart TV delivers a user-friendly experience: the easy-to-use remote and dual-band wireless make it fast and easy to access your favorite content. Roku search allows you to easily search across top streaming channels by title, actor or directly and now includes voice search. This 40" 1080p 60Hz LED HDTV has three HDMI inputs for connecting your Game console, Cable box or even HD Antenna. Cast personal media directly to the TV from your smartphone or tablet using the free Roku mobile app for iOS and android. This RCA ROKU LED HDTV features a sleek modern design with its quad-pedestal stand. It enhances any room in the house. With a true 16:9 aspect ratio for viewing your movies the way that the director intended. Mount the unit on your wall or set it on top of your entertainment center. Works with the Google Assistant.
name: RCA 40" Class FHD 1080P Roku LED Smart TV (RTR4060-W)

reviews.topPositiveReview.reviewText: My husband and i love this smart t.v. been working, easy set up since we got it! I watched fed ex bring it straight from the truck also!! Nice and clear

shortDescription: Make everyone in the family happy when you have this TCL Roku TV. It puts all your viewing favorites in one place. This TCL 40" smart TV gives you seamless access to over 500,000 movies and shows. Connect your cable box, gaming console, and other devices through a simple, intuitive interface in a sleek modern design. There are three HDMI inputs and it has dual-band Wi-Fi. Enjoy Dolby Digital Plus sound for all of your entertainment for greater immersion. This TCL 1080p Roku Smart LED TV also comes with a quad pedestal stand.
name: TCL 40" Class 1080P FHD LED Roku Smart TV 3 Series 40S325

reviews.topNegativeReview.reviewText: It's doing nothing. Won't turn on at all. Changed batteries in the remote, checked plug and connection. There's a fan plugged into the same outlet and it's working. I changed outlets and nothing! Just a giant black screen to stare at. Will contact the manufacturer tomorrow.
reviews.topPositiveReview.reviewText: I've been thinking about getting a TV for my bedroom for a while now though, I didn't want to have to get another cable box for it. So, I knew I wanted another smart TV and after looking at a lot of 40" smart TV I decided to go with this Roku TV. Not only does it have all the channels I watch as well as Youtube, Prime, Hulu, etc. but it also has the Xfinity Stream app. So, I can watch all my DVR recordings as well as Live TV

shortDescription: Versatility and performance collide with the new D-Series FHD Smart TV that comes loaded with a full array backlight for better contrast and uniformity, brilliant 1080p Full HD resolution and an ultra-fast VIZIO IQ processor with support for immersive audio pass-through for Dolby Atmos and DTS:X. Game on with the V-Gaming Engine that enables next-level gaming performance with features like Variable Refresh Rate with AMD FreeSync, auto game mode, low-latency gaming, and newly added gaming menu. D-Series blends power, speed and versatile size. Stream it all with the award-winning SmartCast platform loaded with the best selection of built-in apps including WatchFree+ that lets you enjoy free access to live TV and hundreds of free channels right out of the box. SmartCast also works with Apple AirPlay 2 and Chromecast built-in, offering unparalleled entertainment in a size that fits your lifestyle.
name: VIZIO 43" Class D-Series FHD LED Smart TV D43f-J04

It was very easy to set up right out of the box. The two legs screw into the bottom with two screws that are in the package for the remote. The remote comes with two batteries so you can use it immediately. The on-screen set up was quick and easy to follow. The TV connected to our internet as soon as we entered the password. The TV is very light so you can move it or hold it on the wall with no problem. The picture is exactly what you have come to expect from these flat screen tv's..it's great. The colors are sharp. The frame around the outside is thin and does not distract from your viewing. There are two speakers with volume that goes up to 100. We are currently using this with no sound system and are happy with the factory sound. There is an interactive tour and set up guide that you can access online that is easy to refer to and helps you learn about the many settings you have to choose from. reviews.topPositiveReview.reviewText: I plugged this TV in and automatically picked up the internet; then it asked for the internet password, updated, and was ready to go. There are so many channels, and the stations are right on the main menu, so it is effortless to find your favorite show. It doesn't buffer, and the program comes on immediately. The picture is clear, bright, and you can adjust to your liking, and the sound is good for only the tv speakers. The stand was very easy to screw on with included screws. Remote also came with batteries.

shortDescription: Bring all your favorite TV shows, movies, games, and media content to life in vivid, vibrant Full HD 1080p with twice the resolution of standard HD TV. Access all your favorites with intuitive Smart TV features and built-in Wi-Fi for a more interactive, more connected home entertainment experience. Enhance your home entertainment experience with SAMSUNG Soundbar. Instantly hear clearer dialogue and deeper bass. Plus, stream music by simply connecting your smart devices via Bluetooth.
name: SAMSUNG 32" Class FHD (1080P) Smart LED TV (UN32N5300)

shortDescription: Journey into an incredibly realistic landscape as eight million pixels of brilliant color and clarity materialize before your eyes. Sceptre 4K Ultra High-Definition displays have four times the number of pixels as a Full HD display, turning your shows into an epic UHD viewing experience. The unequalled color and clear brilliance of 4k will provide more natural and lifelike images than have ever been viewed on a 50-inch screen. Three HDMI ports allow you to connect up to three devices at once, so you can stream, browse and listen to all of your favorite multimedia. The HDMI 2.0 ports allow you to seamlessly stream 4k video to get the most rewarding viewing experience that is available on the market. Explore your apps on this giant LED screen once you connect your smartphone or tablet to the Mobile High-Definition Link (MHL) port (HDMI 1). The innovative USB port further expands functionality, allowing users to listen to music and view digital pictures quickly and conveniently.
name: Sceptre 50" Class 4K UHD LED TV U515CV-U

The fourth port can do 4K resolution but is limited to 30 hz but that doesn\'t matter as this HDMI port should be used with a soundbar that has an HDMI ARC/CEC connection. My cheap soundbar\'s ARC refused to work correctly (Grand Teton from Amazon) with the TV but it was an issue with the soundbar itself. The speakers built into the TV are awful like they are on most flat screen televisions. Get a decent soundbar to pair up with the unit. Also this is the only LCD TV that came as a "dumb" TV which I was specifically looking for. Rokus that are built into the TV run very slow and are barely usable. Grab a Roku streaming stick   to add to this TV as it\'s the least expensive Roku model that has the improved dual core processor and can put out a 4k 60 hz signal. If you\'re buying this TV it\'s only for the picture itself. Plan on joining a soundbar with HDMI ARC/CEC support so the TV can control its power and volume. Be sure not to get the cheapest one you can find get a decent soundbar with HDMI for $70-$80. Even really pricey televisions need soundbars as the manufacturer is forced to install tiny thin speakers that point downwards. By adding a decent HDMI soundbar you\'ll get a great picture along with good sound. Don\'t use the built in speaker on any flat screen television. Even if you\'re forced to get a flat screen with built in Roku functions still pick up a Roku streaming stick   and use that instead you\'ll appreciate how much faster Roku runs and it\'s remote can be programmed to operate this TV just use Sony codes to do it with and also it will be an RF remote which doesn\'t have to be pointed at anything when you go to operate the Roku system. If you enable the CEC function on the Roku if the TV isn\'t on its HDMI input press any button on the remote (not power or volume buttons use any of the other ones) This is a $200 flat-screen with a great picture on it spent another $120 to add a decent soundbar and the upgraded Roku stick (they are only $40). For a total of $320 I have a setup that has great video and sound along with a Roku that operates way faster and smoother than one that\'s built into the TV. My setup rivals brand name "smart" flat screens hands down. If you follow my recommendations even if you have to buy a "smart" TV you\'ll have a much better experience than using the built in speakers or Roku. Tech support for this brand were quick to respond to me and made me feel more confident about buying such an inexpensive flat screen. One final thing. The new TV wouldn\'t fit on my dresser so I found replacement metal legs/feet that bolt into the 200 mm x 200 mm vesa mounting holes which placed the feet much closer together and even allowed 5 degree tilting into the TV. The new legs were only $18 a stand takes up twice as much space and costs ~$35. I guess my total setup cost $340, an affordable price for great picture/sound.', 'reviewTitle': 'Great image add decent Roku', 'negativeFeedback': 0, 'positiveFeedback': 6, 'userNickname': 'Currie', shortDescription: Binge on movies and TV episodes, news, sports, music and more! We insisted on 4K Ultra High Definition for this 50” LED TV, bringing out more lifelike color, texture and detail. We also partnered with Roku to bring you the best possible content with thousands of channels to choose from, conveniently presented through your own customizable home screen. Watch via cable, satellite, HDTV antenna or just start streaming from your favorite app. Like the sound of your own voice? You can actually use it with the Roku mobile app to search for the title, artist, actor or director, or just go old-school with our handy remote. We handle all software updates too, automatically, so all you have to worry about is what to watch. Lose yourself in the ultimate viewing experience. We're onn.™ to something here. Say goodbye to stressful decision-making and fear of the electronics aisle. Our mission is simple…to deliver great products and make it easy. Choose onn. and get back to using your brainpower for the important things in life like pondering the question, "What should I binge watch this weekend?”
name: onn. 50” Class 4K UHD (2160P) LED Roku Smart TV HDR (100012585)

I've always been curious about Roku TVs and could never gather enough information about them to make a informed decision to purchase one and honestly have realized I wish I hadn't waited so long. 
 First, the remote is basic and simple to use. There aren't a ton of unnecessary buttons on it so it's easy for kids to use and understand. Batteries are included and the back of the remote slides off.
 Once you plug it in, you follow the prompts on the screen and is very easy to set up. I used the wireless setting and was able to add my current cable provider. I get lots of channels so I can view shows, movies, kids cartoons/kids movies/shows. You can get local channels and current different news channels. There are some channels that cost money with a subscription. I have it set up so my kids can't order anything (you can set a 4 digit pin) and I'd like to add that I think it's a wonderful feature. Another great thing about this Roku tv is that there are games on there! Some are free and others a one time fee. You can add channels for easy access.
 This tv has great volume control (volume is on the side of the remote). We keep the volume level at 8 and it's suitable for everyone. 
 The picture is sharp and clear, colors are vivid. Is it the best on the market? No but there are definitely no complaints about it at all. 
 This tv can be wall mounted (all hardware is included) or can sit on a stand. The legs on it are extremely sturdy and don't wobble. 
 I honestly couldn't be more pleased with this tv. I definitely recommend this tv for anyone wanting to cut the cord. There's literally so many channels that everyone in the family can be happy with. reviews.topPositiveReview.reviewText: I purchased this tv a a quick replacent from my Vizio that stopped working unexpectedly. The quality is almost as good. However the price was great for this size. My husband loves all The ROKU channels that comes with the tv. Great smart tv for the money. I would recommend this product. And when I move shortly I will be purchasing another one to put in our new home.

shortDescription: If you love movies, shows, sports and gaming, then the R6E3 4K UHD Smart Hisense Roku TV is perfect for presenting your favorite entertainment in a whole new way. Featuring 4K Ultra High Definition resolution, the R6E3 packs incredible detail into an HDR-compatible display that boosts contrast and color. With Motion Rate processing tech, you can enjoy the fastest action without lag or judder. The Hisense Roku TV serves up a massive library of premium content at the touch of a button. Simple to set-up and easy-to-use, connect to the internet, activate, and start streaming
name: Hisense 43" Class 4K UHD LED LCD Roku Smart TV HDR R6 Series 43R6E3

reviews.topPositiveReview.reviewText: I purchased this television to replace a smaller 32 inch Hisense, which should tell you I like this model very much.  The price was comparable to other brands of similar size. Setup was quick and easy and, like the smaller version, the picture quality sound and navigation was perfect.  I highly recommend Hisense.
reviews.topPositiveReview.reviewTitle: Perfect for Newly Decorated Guest Room

shortDescription: The TCL 4-Series Roku TV offers stunning 4K picture quality with four times the resolution of Full HD for enhanced clarity and detail, as well as endless entertainment with thousands of streaming channels. High dynamic range (HDR) technology delivers bright and accurate colors for a lifelike viewing experience. In addition, your favorite HD shows, movies, and sporting events are enhanced to near Ultra HD resolution with 4K Upscaling. Your favorite broadcast TV, streaming channels, gaming console and other devices are front-and-center within a simple, customizable home screen. There’s no more flipping through inputs or wading through complicated menus. The super-simple remote—with about half the number of buttons on a traditional TV remote—puts you in control of your favorite entertainment and includes one-touch shortcuts to popular channels like Netflix.
name: TCL 50" Class 4-Series 4K UHD HDR Smart Roku TV - 50S451

reviews.topNegativeReview.reviewText: Piece of Junk! So flimsy that when I went behind my TV my leg barley touch it and knocked it over and busted my 1 month old TV. The legs are made of a cheap plastic and definitely not strong enough to hold up a 65 inch TV! It broke the plastic screen and now all you can see on the screen is lights and cracked lines all through the screen. I am so upset. I'm going to call the company and see if they will do right and refund me for this poor quality of a tv.
reviews.topNegativeReview.reviewTitle: Flimsy piece of Junk for a TV`

reviews.topPositiveReview.reviewText: Although the volume needs to be higher I did find that if you go into settings. It fixes that. Anyways. I ordered a 58in tv was a hiSense brand tv and after getting it mounted and turned on the screen was broke. So much for fed ex delivery. But I was able to get it refunded and I took the gift card and went for the TCL 65” smart Roku tv. Got it all set up and have been happy ever since. Now. Let see if it lasts long. Lol keeping fingers crossed but I do have to say. TCL is turning into a quality brand now.  I love the picture!!!
reviews.topPositiveReview.reviewTitle: Forget HiSense tvs. TCL is way to go!!

shortDescription: JVC 43" Class 4K (2160p) Roku Smart TV (LT-43MAW595) is more than a smart TV - it's a better TV. All of your entertainment is in one place with access to over 500,000 movies, TV episodes, and more than 5,000 streaming channels. Start streaming your favorite shows, access your cable box or HD antenna, even fire up your gaming console - all from your home screen. With Featured Free on your home screen, you're one click away from hundreds of free movies, TV episodes, and live news from channels like The Roku Channel, ABC, CW and more. Easily search across top channels for results ranked by price. Use the free Roku mobile app for iOS or Android devices to search by voice, cast personal media or video, and control your TV.
name: JVC 43" Class 4K UHD 2160p LED Roku Smart TV LT-43MAW595

reviews.topNegativeReview.reviewText: Broke already and hasn't even been a year yet. Purchased February 24th last year. 1st Aline appeared in the middle of the screen after a few months in. Wasn't sure what to do because i purchased it on the Walmart app and didn't keep the box either. But was like oh well it's a thin line, at least it still works. Could be worse. Well 2 days ago go to turn on the tv and the sound is playing but the screen is black. From what I've read this is a common issue with this particular tv. I think it should have a year warranty but I'm not sure how to follow up on that. I wouldn't recommend this tv because how quickly it broke. I will say it had a great picture and I loved it right until I didn't because it hasn't even lasted a year
