reviews.topPositiveReview.reviewText: We were NOT actually SHOPPING for a new TV. We did wish we had smartTV features and a somewhat larger screen than our 32-inch flat-screen, but were not on the hunt for a newer one. When we saw a name-brand JVC 43-inch smart TV for UNDER $200, we couldn't resist. It is GREAT! Easy to set up, easy to use, great picture and sound -- we LOVE it!  The design of the remote isn't the best one we've ever used but it works and is simple. If we had it to do over again, we DEFINITELY WOULD BUY IT AGAIN.
reviews.topPositiveReview.reviewTitle: A GREAT BUY, great price, works great! LOVE IT!

shortDescription: Binge on movies and TV episodes, news, sports, music and more! We insisted on 1080P Full High Definition for this 43” LED TV, bringing out more lifelike color, texture and detail. We also partnered with Roku to bring you the best possible content with thousands of channels to choose from, conveniently presented through your own customizable home screen. Watch via cable, satellite, HDTV antenna or just start streaming from your favorite app. Like the sound of your own voice? You can actually use it with the Roku mobile app to search for the title, artist, actor or director, or just go old-school with our handy remote. We handle all software updates too, automatically, so all you have to worry about is what to watch. Lose yourself in the ultimate viewing experience. We're onn.™ to something here. Say goodbye to stressful decision-making and fear of the electronics aisle. Our mission is simple…to deliver great products and make it easy. Choose onn. and get back to using your brainpower for the important things in life like pondering the question, "What should I binge watch this weekend?”
name: onn. 43” Class FHD (1080P) LED Roku Smart TV (100069992)

shortDescription: With a Sceptre 55-inch LED 4K Ultra HD TV (U550CV-U), entertainment is transformed into an epic adventure. The unequaled color and clear brilliance of 4K (3840 x 2160 or over eight million pixels) will provide more natural and lifelike images than have ever been viewed on a 55-inch screen. Four HDMI ports allow you to connect up to four devices at once, so you can stream, browse and listen to all of your favorite multimedia. Equipped with HDMI 2.0 ports, the U55 can seamlessly stream 4K video to provide you the most rewarding viewing experience that is available on the market. The innovative USB port further expands functionality.
name: Sceptre 55" Class 4K UHD LED TV HDR U550CV-U

reviews.topNegativeReview.reviewText: Was shipped to my home thinking it would be well taken care of during shipping….boy was I wrong. It got delivered today and I just took it out of the box to hook up. Upon plugging it in and turning it on I had a horrible surprise. It was broke. Screen was barely attached to the base. Not happy at all
reviews.topPositiveReview.reviewText: This is my second Sceptre TV. First was a 50 inch that I purchased six years ago. Never had an issue with it, in fact we still use it daily in the kids playroom. Just picked up a 55 inch 4K for less money than what I paid for the 50 inch TV 6 years ago, and I thought I got a good deal then. For the price- you cant beat it. I use an Apple TV for both, so I have no need for a smart TV.

shortDescription: Enjoy a viewing experience that is twice the clarity of standard HD TVs with the Samsung 40" Class N5200 Smart Full HD TV. Get crisp, beautiful Full HD video and enjoy a more colorful viewing experience with PurColor from this 40" LED Smart TV. Intuitive smart features allow you to browse the web and cast a smartphone screen or compatible apps to the TV. Bring all your favorite TV shows, movies, games and media content to life in vivid, vibrant Full HD 1080p with twice the resolution of standard HD TV. See images as they were meant to be seen with enriched colors - even with older, non-HD content. Analyzing original content with an advanced algorithm, Digital Clean View gives you higher quality images with less distortion. Dividing the screen into zones, Micro Dimming Pro analyzes each one for deeper blacks and purer whites. Plug your favorite entertainment and media into your TV – watch videos, play music, or view photos through a USB connection. Easily access your streaming services all in one place using the Samsung Remote Control. Have several smart devices to manage? No problem. Simply download SmartThings App on your smart phone to control your connected devices all in one screen. Discover the power of the Samsung 40" Class N5200 Smart Full HD TV.
name: Samsung 40" Class N5200 Smart Full HD TV (2019), UN40N5200AFXZA

shortDescription: Binge on movies and TV episodes, news, sports, music and more! We insisted on 4K Ultra High Definition for this 55” LED TV, bringing out more lifelike color, texture and detail. We also partnered with Roku to bring you the best possible content with thousands of channels to choose from, conveniently presented through your own customizable home screen. Watch via cable, satellite, HDTV antenna or just start streaming from your favorite app. Like the sound of your own voice? You can actually use it with the Roku mobile app to search for the title, artist, actor or director, or just go old-school with our handy remote. We handle all software updates too, automatically, so all you have to worry about is what to watch. Lose yourself in the ultimate viewing experience. We're onn.™ to something here. Say goodbye to stressful decision-making and fear of the electronics aisle. Our mission is simple…to deliver great products and make it easy. reviews.topNegativeReview.reviewText: This tv had a humongous black line through it when we got it. It was gifted and they didn't open it until after the 30 day return. They were unable to return tv and we were told we needed to go through the warranty. Warranty company is through Walmart. This has been a horrible experience. Tried to call the number… no answer and never received a call back. Tried emailing and they were very slow to respond.  I have been trying to get return instructions for 4 days.

shortDescription: Escape into awesome entertainment with the VIZIO V-Series 4K UHD Smart TV. With epic 4K UHD picture quality,  Dolby Vision Bright Mode, HDR10, a full array backlight, and active pixel tuning, V-Series provides crystal-clear and sharp picture quality. The next-gen speed and power of the VIZIO IQ Active processor brings astonishing detail and vibrancy to your viewing experience.   Take your gaming to a whole new level with the V-Gaming engine which enables sub 10ms input lag, 4K 48-60 fps Variable Refresh Rate, Auto Game Mode, and a newly added gaming menu. Stream it all with the award-winning SmartCast platform loaded with the best selection of built-in apps including WatchFree+ that lets you enjoy free access to live TV and hundreds of free channels right out of the box. Pair your favorite Bluetooth headphones and hear every word – uninterrupted. SmartCast also works with Apple AirPlay 2 and Chromecast built-in, offering unparalleled entertainment in a size that fits your lifestyle. V-series is everything you need and more in a Smart TV delivering a standout experience at an unmatched price.
name: VIZIO 43" Class V-Series 4K UHD LED Smart TV V435-J01

{'reviewId': '288191576', 'rating': 1, 'reviewSubmissionTime': '10/14/2022', 'reviewText': "If I could give this 0 stars I would. My previous tv was a Vizio and it has work beautifully for 10 years. This is why when I decided to get a new tv with a larger screen I got another Vizio. But this is a piece of junk. reviews.topNegativeReview.reviewText: If I could give this 0 stars I would. My previous tv was a Vizio and it has work beautifully for 10 years. This is why when I decided to get a new tv with a larger screen I got another Vizio. But this is a piece of junk. It work perfect for about  9 months. Now when it does turn on it has a 6” strip down the middle that is all messed up and white dotted light that run across the screen. I have never left a review on an item before but this is ridiculous, a $400 tv should work for more than 9 months. I used to trust Vizio's products but not any more. So mad and disappointed.

reviews.topPositiveReview.reviewText: This 70" Vizio Smart Tv is everything I hoped it would be. Giant clear screen! The price was just right. I used my Sams Bonus Rewards for most of it!  We had it mounted on a pull out swivel mount also purchased at Sams. Added a sound bar and it is theater quality.  We can watch tv anywhere now.

shortDescription: If you love movies, shows, sports and gaming, then the R6E 4K UHD Smart Hisense Roku TV is perfect for presenting your favorite entertainment in a whole new way. Featuring 4K Ultra High Definition resolution, the R6E3 packs incredible detail into an HDR-compatible display that boosts contrast and color. With Motion Rate processing tech, you can enjoy the fastest action without lag or judder. The Hisense Roku TV serves up a massive library of premium content at the touch of a button. Simple to set-up and easy-to-use, connect to the internet, activate, and start streaming
name: Hisense 50" Class 4K UHD LED LCD Roku Smart TV HDR R6 Series 50R6E3

reviews.topPositiveReview.reviewText: I own other Hisense TVs and wanted this 50".  I'm very happy with it as I knew I would be. For those who want to know the measurements so that you know what size tv stand you can use, my stand is 40" wide. I took the off chance and tried it and it worked. The legs measure 38" across and 9.5" deep so I have and inch on each side left until I decide to get another stand in the future. The screen itself is 44' across, 23.5" tall (28" tall from the legs to the top of the screen) and about 50.5" diagonal.  I hope this helps many of you with those questions. I really like this tv and hope you enjoy the picture and sound quality that I have come to know with mine.

shortDescription: The TCL 4-Series Roku TV offers stunning 4K picture quality with four times the resolution of Full HD for enhanced clarity and detail, as well as endless entertainment with thousands of streaming channels. High dynamic range (HDR) technology delivers bright and accurate colors for a lifelike viewing experience. In addition, your favorite HD shows, movies, and sporting events are enhanced to near Ultra HD resolution with 4K Upscaling. Your favorite broadcast TV, streaming channels, gaming console and other devices are front-and-center within a simple, customizable home screen. There’s no more flipping through inputs or wading through complicated menus. The super-simple remote—with about half the number of buttons on a traditional TV remote—puts you in control of your favorite entertainment and includes one-touch shortcuts to popular channels like Netflix.
name: TCL 55" Class 4-Series 4K UHD HDR Smart Roku TV - 55S451

reviews.topNegativeReview.reviewText:
Like so many others, broken screen. Get it out of the box, set it up, turn it on, broken screen. There was NO DAMAGE to the box at all.  It's a lot of fun spending time, unboxing, setting it up, reboxing, taking it back to Walmart, wait at CS desk (or send back by UPS). 
Why waste time?
reviews.topPositiveReview.reviewText: Although the volume needs to be higher I did find that if you go into settings. It fixes that. Anyways. I ordered a 58in tv was a hiSense brand tv and after getting it mounted and turned on the screen was broke. So much for fed ex delivery. But I was able to get it refunded and I took the gift card and went for the TCL 65” smart Roku tv. Got it all set up and have been happy ever since. Now. Let see if it lasts long. Lol keeping fingers crossed but I do have to say. TCL is turning into a quality brand now.  I love the picture!!!
reviews.topPositiveReview.reviewTitle: Forget HiSense tvs. TCL is way to go!!

shortDescription: The 4-Series 4K TCL Android TV delivers stunning Ultra HD picture quality with four times the resolution of Full HD for enhanced clarity and detail, as well as endless entertainment with thousands of streaming apps. Watch your entertainment favorites in one place, with seamless access to over 700,000 movies and TV episodes, your cable box, gaming console, and other devices—all from a simple, speedy home screen. Enjoy entertainment, get answers, and control devices around your home using Google Assistant. Plus, with Chromecast built-in, you can easily cast movies, shows, and photos from your Android or iOS device to your TCL Android TV. Connect all your favorite devices with the multiple HDMI inputs. Cord cutters can access free, over-the-air HD content with the built-in tuner or watch live TV from popular cable-replacement services like YouTube TV, Sling, Hulu and more.
name: TCL 50" Class 4-Series 4K UHD HDR Smart Android TV – 50S434

Sometimes when it does turn on, you get the title screen saying "Smart TV - Power by Tizen" but wont get any further.', 'reviewTitle': 'Terrible.', 'negativeFeedback': 0, 'positiveFeedback': 0, 'userNickname': 'Roberto', 'photos': [{'caption': None, 'id': 'afd09da6-9403-4432-af64-893f1404e029', 'sizes': {'normal': {'id': 'normal', 'url': 'https://i5.walmartimages.com/dfw/6e29e393-5c23/k2-_cfc108eb-277d-4e99-846d-138a63ff8e68.v1.bin'}, 'thumbnail': {'id': 'thumbnail', 'url': 'https://i5.walmartimages.com/dfw/6e29e393-5c23/k2-_cfc108eb-277d-4e99-846d-138a63ff8e68.v1.bin?odnWidth=150&odnHeight=150&odnBg=ffffff'}}}], 'badges': [{'badgeType': 'Custom', 'id': 'VerifiedPurchaser', 'contentType': 'REVIEW', 'glassBadge': {'id': 'VerifiedPurchaser', 'text': 'Verified Purchaser'}}], 'clientResponses': [{'date': None, 'department': None, 'logoImage': 'https://s3.amazonaws.com/stratos-logos/logos/Samsung.png', 'name': None, 'response': ' Hey Roberto,

We are sorry to hear about your TU7000 TV screen going black. Samsung prides itself on high-quality products and a great customer experience. Please know we are here to help you.

If your TV has a black screen even when it's on, please try these troubleshooting steps for your blank screen issue:

1. Press the Home button on the remote.

If the menu appears, the TV is powered on but is either not on the correct source or not receiving a signal. If the menu does not appear, the TV may have power issues.

Check the red standby light, a little red light at the edge of the TV that you aim the remote at. In everyday use, the red standby light is on when the TV is off (indicating the TV is on standby), and the red standby light is off when the TV is in use (or doesn't have power).

2. Confirm the TV is set to the same source as the external device.

For instance, if your cable box is connected to HDMI 1, set the TV source to HDMI 1.
If the TV is set to the correct source but there is still no image, unplug and reconnect the AV connections one cable at a time from both ends of each cable. If there's any damage to the cable, it will need to be replaced.

After reconnecting the external device, please turn it off and back on.

3. Test the HDMI cable.

Some TVs have an HDMI cable test. Some models only have this test after a software update, and older models do not have it. If your model does not have this test or is not connected by HDMI, skip to the next step.

The test is designed for HDMI cords less than 6 feet long and may not give accurate results on long cords.

To perform the test, make sure the TV's source is still on the HDMI setting for the cable you want to test, and then navigate to Settings > Support > Self Diagnosis > Signal Information > HDMI Cable Test > Start Test.

If the test says, the cable is bad, replace the cable. Service is not required.

4. Test different external devices.

The final thing to rule out is the external device you're using. Try connecting to a different device or using a different source port. If you could not test the cable in the previous step, try swapping the cable, too.

If the TV can display a picture in any other setup, then you've ruled the TV out as the cause of the issue. Keep trying various setups until you identify the device or cable that is not working and troubleshoot or replace it.

The TV will need service if the issue persists after these steps. Please get in touch with us so that we can better investigate your issue and assist you towards a solution or replacement. Please call us at 1-800-SAMSUNG, 8 AM - 12 AM EST, seven days a week. Our LiveChat agents are also available by clicking on the 'Support' link on our website.

~ Samsung Advisor '}], 'syndicationSource': None}, {'reviewId': '253006320', 'rating': 1, 'reviewSubmissionTime': '2/15/2021', 'reviewText': "Purchased this tv a couple of weeks ago (February 2). I've ordered this exact same TV three times.  The first two artived with cracked screens and the third one has a dead spot as shown in the pic.

Not sure if these issues are due to horrible shipping or a bad batch of TVs Wal-Mart is dumping at a reasonable price. 

I will never buy another TV from Wal-Mart but I'm over packing and shipping bad units. I'll see if they will give a partial refund and provide an update of possible. 

Bummed, again....
reviews.topPositiveReview.reviewText: The TV came perfectly wrapped  with no scratches or damages. After mounting, very little to no adjustments were needed. It seems to auto adjust picture quality. It was noticed that there are sound differentials between stations/pictures and the sound has to be adjusted up or down. Especially while viewing streaming apps. Unlike the 55 inch. Not sure why that is. Other than that, enjoying the TV quality.

shortDescription: SAMSUNG 43" Class 4K Crystal UHD (2160P) LED Smart TV with HDR UN43TU7000 -  Get enhanced smart capabilities with the TU7000. Crystal Processor 4K automatically upscales your favorite movies, TV shows and sports events to 4K. Smart TV powered by Tizen lets you find content and navigate streaming services easily. PurColor fine tunes colors while HDR steps up to millions of shades of color that go beyond what HDTV can offer. And Direct Lit backlighting technology sharpens visuals and improves clarity.
name: SAMSUNG 43" Class 4K Crystal UHD (2160P) LED Smart TV with HDR UN43TU7000B

Plus, with Roku TV, it's easy to watch what you love with quick access to thousands of streaming channels, and live TV. More than a smart TV, the Hisense 58" Class 4K UHD HDR Roku Smart TV is a better TV.

[{'reviewId': '289699165', 'rating': 5, 'reviewSubmissionTime': '10/28/2022', 'reviewText': "I recently purchased this TV in store and price matched it to the Black Friday Early Access deals price for $198 so hear me out.. the reviews for this TV are awful but most of them are shipping related. I would not recommend shipping a TV but always getting it in store. As for quality I'm very impressed for the price I paid. I personally accepted that it was a hit or miss and I could purchase the Allstate 4 year plan on top of it. So I feel like doing that I got my values worth on a TV that actually is pretty nice. I will say though I could understand how in shipping things are damaged and you could be very mad. But I was lucky enough to have it in stock at my store and to just bring it home.", 'reviewTitle': "don't trust a reviews!", 'negativeFeedback': 0, 'positiveFeedback': 0, 'userNickname': 'Jacqueline', 'photos': [{'caption': None, 'id': '30c1a89d-c1ac-431a-ae49-0a06fe1fbc37', 'sizes': {'normal': {'id': 'normal', 'url': 'https://i5.walmartimages.com/dfw/6e29e393-3bf6/k2-_b4ca46aa-4680-4b41-9a8b-c06974b5b2c3.v1.bin'}, 'thumbnail': {'id': 'thumbnail', 'url': 'https://i5.walmartimages.com/dfw/6e29e393-3bf6/k2-_b4ca46aa-4680-4b41-9a8b-c06974b5b2c3.v1.bin?odnWidth=150&odnHeight=150&odnBg=ffffff'}}}], 'badges': [{'badgeType': 'Custom', 'id': 'VerifiedPurchaser', 'contentType': 'REVIEW', 'glassBadge': {'id': 'VerifiedPurchaser', 'text': 'Verified Purchaser'}}], 'clientResponses': None, 'syndicationSource': None}, {'reviewId': '290603294', 'rating': 5, 'reviewSubmissionTime': '11/6/2022', 'reviewText': 'My TV was 10 yo,I definitely needed to upgrade, couldn't be happier with my 58" Hisense 4K Roku. The picture is great,and infinitely adjustable,the sound is good,but I am a soundbar/subwoofer guy anyway,for that theater experience,and thumping music. Trying to get to used to a remote without numbers,not even with my universal remote,but I'll adapt. One thing is that I cut the cord on cable,I get 60 broadcast channels,and started streaming,but with a marginal Wi-Fi signal,but free. reviews.topPositiveReview.reviewText: I recently purchased this TV in store and price matched it to the Black Friday Early Access deals price for $198 so hear me out.. the reviews for this TV are awful but most of them are shipping related. I would not recommend shipping a TV but always getting it in store. As for quality I'm very impressed for the price I paid. I personally accepted that it was a hit or miss and I could purchase the Allstate 4 year plan on top of it. So I feel like doing that I got my values worth on a TV that actually is pretty nice. I will say though I could understand how in shipping things are damaged and you could be very mad. But I was lucky enough to have it in stock at my store and to just bring it home.

shortDescription: Escape into awesome entertainment with the VIZIO V-Series 4K UHD Smart TV. With epic 4K UHD picture quality,  Dolby Vision Bright Mode, HDR10, a full array backlight, and active pixel tuning, V-Series provides crystal-clear and sharp picture quality. The next-gen speed and power of the VIZIO IQ Active processor brings astonishing detail and vibrancy to your viewing experience.   Take your gaming to a whole new level with the V-Gaming engine which enables sub 10ms input lag, 4K 48-60 fps Variable Refresh Rate, Auto Game Mode, and a newly added gaming menu. Stream it all with the award-winning SmartCast platform loaded with the best selection of built-in apps including WatchFree+ that lets you enjoy free access to live TV and hundreds of free channels right out of the box. Pair your favorite Bluetooth headphones and hear every word – uninterrupted. SmartCast also works with Apple AirPlay 2 and Chromecast built-in, offering unparalleled entertainment in a size that fits your lifestyle. V-series is everything you need and more in a Smart TV delivering a standout experience at an unmatched price.
name: VIZIO 50" Class V-Series 4K UHD LED Smart TV V505-J09

reviews.topNegativeReview.reviewText: If I could give this 0 stars I would. My previous tv was a Vizio and it has work beautifully for 10 years. This is why when I decided to get a new tv with a larger screen I got another Vizio. But this is a piece of junk. It work perfect for about  9 months. Now when it does turn on it has a 6” strip down the middle that is all messed up and white dotted light that run across the screen. I have never left a review on an item before but this is ridiculous, a $400 tv should work for more than 9 months. I used to trust Vizio's products but not any more. So mad and disappointed.

reviews.topPositiveReview.reviewText: This 70" Vizio Smart Tv is everything I hoped it would be. Giant clear screen! The price was just right. I used my Sams Bonus Rewards for most of it!  We had it mounted on a pull out swivel mount also purchased at Sams. Added a sound bar and it is theater quality.  We can watch tv anywhere now.

shortDescription: Experience Quantum Dot technology in our newest premium TV. Our new QLED panel leaps beyond the standard LED screen by adding a quantum filter that precisely controls color output, giving you more vibrant colors, deeper blacks and brighter images than ever before. QLED's sharp contrast and upscaling abilities are hallmarks of the step-up from regular LED, granting your 4K and HDR content extra punch and clarity. With 120hz effective refresh rate, you'll experience sharp images while watching sports, or any fast-moving action for smooth on-screen motion. We've also added Dolby Vision® and Dolby Atmos® technologies to give you the most remarkable, immersive experience possible. Dolby Vision HDR maximizes QLED's display potential for a more lifelike and ultravivid picture, while Dolby Atmos introduces audio that surrounds and moves all around you with breathtaking realism. Plus, local dimming creates intense blacks and stunning contrasts with multiple LED zones. Never miss a detail, even in the darkest of scenes.What about that content, you ask? We've partnered with industry-leading Roku to bring you some of the best shows, movies, media and music available. You'll have thousands of channels to choose from, conveniently presented through your own customizable home screen. Watch via cable, satellite, HDTV antenna or just start streaming from your favorite app. Control your entertainment or even change channels with the Roku voice remote. We'll handle all the software updates as well, automatically, so all you have to worry about is what to watch. Lose yourself in the ultimate viewing experience. Watch onn.™We're onn. to something here. We took the hassle out of buying electronics and built a brand that's fresh and simple. With delightful pops of color, finding the right product has never been easier. Say goodbye to stressful decision-making and fear of the electronics aisle. Our mission is simple… to deliver great products and make it easy. Choose onn. and get back to using your brainpower for the important things in life… like pondering the question, "What should I binge watch this weekend?"
name: onn. 55” QLED 4K UHD (2160p) Roku Smart TV with Dolby Atmos, Dolby Vision, Local Dimming, 120hz Effective Refresh Rate, and HDR (100071701)

shortDescription: JVC 58" Class 4K UHD 2160p Roku Smart TV LT-58MAW595 is more than a smart TV - it's a better TV. All of your entertainment is in one place with access to over 500,000 movies, TV episodes, and more than 5,000 streaming channels. Start streaming your favorite shows, access your cable box or HD antenna, even fire up your gaming console - all from your home screen. With Featured Free on your home screen, you're one click away from hundreds of free movies, TV episodes, and live news from channels like The Roku Channel, ABC, CW and more. Easily search across top channels for results ranked by price. Use the free Roku mobile app for iOS or Android devices to search by voice, cast personal media or video, and control your TV. Bring home the JVC 55" Class 4K UHD 2160p Roku Smart TV LT-58MAW595 and treat yourself to a better viewing experience.
name: JVC 58" Class 4K UHD 2160P HDR Roku Smart LED TV (LT-58MAW595)

If we're confusing the product and the carrier, why not also go to Fedex and leave reviews of the TV? My gripe is about the build quality and the packaging method as my box came in perfect condition and was delivered carefully right to my door, but out of box the frame of the TV was clearly bent, meaning the packaging is probably not robust enough for the dimensions and build quality of the TV. I know this is a $300 TV, but it should still be able to survive transport, especially when the outer packaging showed zero damage. 

My issue with the frame was immediately noticeable. On the bottom of the frame, center-right location, just to the side of the JVC logo, the frame wasn't snapped in all the way. There was a major dip, and upon powering, you could see a bright gap of light escaping, like light coming in under a door into a dark room. I had it shipped because my car couldn't fit the box, and therefore I couldn't return it. My only chance was to try to snap the frame back into place, which happened with a relatively light press. However, the frame didn't become completely square. It still shows a dip, especially noticeable when the sun comes through the window and reflects and you see the bent portion of the frame. Additionally, the screen is pushed a bit back at this location. Again, since I can't return it without bugging a friend with a truck for a day, and then roll the dice with a replacement, I'm just going to live with it. The picture is still fine for a 2nd TV. It's just a bummer since it seems to have shipped properly. With other complaints about out-of-box failures, I think JVC needs to consider their build quality and/or their packaging methods, and is most certainly not making me want to be a repeat customer anytime soon. Picture of a straight card (verified with a straight edge which was too awkward to use for photos) aligned on one side of the frame's dip shown so you can see the gap on the opposite side of the card. Also pic of the screen pushed back a bit at this location shown (look at shadow between frame and the blue in 2nd pic). 

Other than this major bummer in build quality, I think the TV, picture quality, and ROKU interface is a great value for the money.", 'reviewTitle': 'A build', 'negativeFeedback': 0, shortDescription: Escape into awesome entertainment with the VIZIO V-Series 4K UHD Smart TV. With epic 4K UHD picture quality,  Dolby Vision Bright Mode, HDR10, a full array backlight, and active pixel tuning, V-Series provides crystal-clear and sharp picture quality. The next-gen speed and power of the VIZIO IQ Active processor brings astonishing detail and vibrancy to your viewing experience.   Take your gaming to a whole new level with the V-Gaming engine which enables sub 10ms input lag, 4K 48-60 fps Variable Refresh Rate, Auto Game Mode, and a newly added gaming menu. Stream it all with the award-winning SmartCast platform loaded with the best selection of built-in apps including WatchFree+ that lets you enjoy free access to live TV and hundreds of free channels right out of the box. Pair your favorite Bluetooth headphones and hear every word – uninterrupted. SmartCast also works with Apple AirPlay 2 and Chromecast built-in, offering unparalleled entertainment in a size that fits your lifestyle. V-series is everything you need and more in a Smart TV delivering a standout experience at an unmatched price.
name: VIZIO 55" Class V-Series 4K UHD LED Smart TV V555-J01

reviews.topPositiveReview.reviewText: This 70" Vizio Smart Tv is everything I hoped it would be. Giant clear screen! The price was just right. I used my Sams Bonus Rewards for most of it!  We had it mounted on a pull out swivel mount also purchased at Sams. Added a sound bar and it is theater quality.  We can watch tv anywhere now.

shortDescription: Made for the Way You Watch                                                                            Dive into a world of free content and personalized recommendations for everyone you share the remote with. Enhance your picture and sound with AI from the α5 Gen5 AI Processor 4K that is engineered to amaze by transforming your regular content into 4K for sharper definition and detail, even on our biggest screens*. Take binge-watching further by customizing your viewing experience with separate accounts and personalized recommendations for every member of your family with webOS 22. And enjoy binge-worthy streaming with built-in access to Netflix, the Apple TV app, Disney+, HBO Max** and to over 300+ free LG Channels*** with everything from comedy to movies to sports. For gamers, you can make it the best gaming experience by quickly adjusting all your game settings in one location with the LG Game Optimizer and Dashboard. Bring your content to life with LG UHD. See a vivid picture every time with LG UHD’s 4K resolution.                                                                                       *Image quality of upscaled content will vary based on the source resolution.                                                                                                    **Internet connection and subscriptions to streaming services are required. HBO Max™ ©2022 Warner Media, LLC. All Rights Reserved. HBO Max is used under license.                                                          ***Number of LG Channels subject to change.

reviews.topNegativeReview.reviewText:
I bought this TV yesterday.  After getting the TV mounted and everything set up, I found out the Spectrum app can't be downloaded on LG.

After years of watching the app on cheaper TVs, I now find out I have to buy a separate streaming device like a ROKU stick or Chromecast just to get the Spectrum app.

In this day and age, why can't LG and Spectrum find a way for the app to be used?  Are there any plans in the works to get this available?
reviews.topNegativeReview.clientResponse: [{'date': None, 'department': None, 'logoImage': None, 'name': 'JaNika Wiley', 'response': "We appreciate your feedback, and we're sorry to hear that you had a negative experience with your LG TV. This information will be shared with our research and development teams for future improvements. ^Nikki\n"}]

reviews.topPositiveReview.reviewTitle: Lovely new member of our family

shortDescription: Binge on movies and TV episodes, news, sports, music and more! We insisted on 4K Ultra High Definition for this 65” LED TV, bringing out more lifelike color, texture and detail than ever before. We also partnered with Roku to bring you the best possible content with thousands of channels to choose from, conveniently presented through your own customizable home screen. Watch via cable, satellite, HDTV antenna or just start streaming from your favorite app. Like the sound of your own voice You can actually use it with the Roku mobile app to search for a title, artist, actor or director, or just go old-school with our handy remote. We handle all software updates too, automatically, so all you have to worry about is what to watch. Lose yourself in the ultimate viewing experience. Watch on with our onn. 4K UHD 65" Smart TV. We're onn. to something here. We took the hassle out of buying electronics and built a brand that's fresh and simple. With delightful pops of color, finding the right product has never been easier. Say goodbye to stressful decision-making and fear of the electronics aisle. Our mission is simple… to deliver great products and make it easy. Choose onn. and get back to using your brainpower for the important things in life like pondering the question, "What should I binge watch this weekend?"
name: onn. 65” Class 4K UHD (2160P) LED Roku Smart TV HDR (100012587)

It takes 2 people to get this TV unboxed. My husband and I got the TV legs on first and set it on our TV stand. There is a quick start guide which tells you how to hook up your 4K UHD LED Roku Smart TV. Keep in mind you will need your own HDMI cable if connecting to a cable service as well as a digital optical cable if connecting to a sound bar. The TV can be watched using just the Roku streaming services or with your cable service or even an antenna. Additional streaming program options are available some free, some charge a small fee. You can also get free music on Pandora. The picture quality is clear as well as the sound. There is an app that you can download onto your phone that allows you to have your remote on your phone. The remote that comes with the TV already has Netflix,Disney,hulu,VUDU buttons on it for your convenience. There are so many choices of programming to choose from that you will never get bored. Hi! Thank you so much for your kind review. We’re glad you love your onn. 65" Roku TV as much as we do!'}], 'syndicationSource': None}, {'reviewId': '230024354', 'rating': 5, 'reviewSubmissionTime': '6/3/2020', 'reviewText': 'I received this onn. 65 Class 4K (2160p) UHD LED Roku Smart TV HDR (100012587) on June 2, 2020. I'm not tech savvy or handy, but I was able to get this unboxed and set up within minutes. Because the TV is large, it is easier to maneuver with another person; however, it's packaged so that you can manage it alone without damaging it. I was happy to see only a small guidebook for quick setup, as this usually means the process will indeed be easy. The only really "mechanical" thing to do is screw the base stands on, and this was easy enough to do since they fit into grooves and you just turn the screws (two on the left, two on the right). Then I plugged the cord into the back of the TV, with the other end going into the wall outlet. Then it turned on and prompted me through the setup - and it was indeed easy. I cannot complain about the packaging, the unpacking, the minimal assembly, or the setup. Have your internet username and password handy - I had my info on my phone on my internet service provider's app. I did not connect a cable box or anything, and that's part of the great thing about these TVs - you can use them as wifi streaming devices or as traditional cable TVs. I was prompted to set up a free Roku account on an internet-connected device (I used my phone - easy) and select the types of programming I like (much of it free, with pay-per-view, local channels, or premium channels also available; the options are many and changeable according to your desires and changing tastes). The whole process was easy, fast, and guided succinctly. I see no drawbacks thus far, and it's certainly the nicest TV I've ever had. The TV really is big! The picture is fantastic and the high definition is impressive. One can really enjoy a rich variety or programming and features on this TV. I can tell this is a unit that will vastly improve the viewer experience, and will probably even make me more interested in programming owing to the quality of the picture and sound. reviews.topNegativeReview.reviewText: Please don't purchase this tv.  The screen went black and I called onn support no response / tech chat results to troubleshoot did not help.  I have had this tv less than a year, called Walmart customer support and it was basically sorry not our problem your 60 return is to late and I had not purchased the extended warranty.  So at this point I may try and get it fixed….or dump it in the trash.  You have been warned!
reviews.topPositiveReview.reviewText: Very happy with my 65” Roku, very easy to navigate, great picture I couldn't be happier .I had bought an LG TV before this one and I ended up taking it back after three days because it was just very hard to navigate. It was just a difficult TV everything about it and I got the Roku on a suggestion from my friend, and I could not be happier.

shortDescription: Step up to the AU8000B with upgraded color and 4K essentials. Dynamic Crystal Color injects each scene with millions of vibrant shades of color, while Crystal Processor 4K with UHD Upscaling elevates all your favorite movies, games and shows to gorgeous 4K quality. Smart TV with Multiple Voice Assistants allows you to use your voice to change channels, adjust the volume, or find quickly find content. Plus 3 HDMI inputs provide plenty of connection options.
name: SAMSUNG 43" Class 4K Crystal UHD (2160P) LED Smart TV with HDR UN43AU8000B

[{'date': None, 'department': None, 'logoImage': None, 'name': 'Samsung Advisor', 'response': "Hi IKnowSomeBody,

Thank you for your purchase and review of the AU8000 TV. I have a few troubleshooting tips for you to try in reference to your Bluetooth device not connecting. 

It appears you are using a device with Norton 360. Your firewall settings may prevent the device from connecting to your Samsung TV. Please check these settings: 

・Open your Norton device security product.
・If you see the My Norton window next to Device Security, click Open.
・In the Norton product main window, click Settings.
・In the Settings window, click Firewall.
・On the General Settings tab, Device Trust row, click Configure.
・In the Network Trust window, under Trust Level, click Full Trust. 

Next, please try repairing your Bluetooth headphone with your TV. Go to Settings > Sound > Sound Output > Bluetooth Speaker List. 

Some things to keep in mind when using Bluetooth headphones:

  - You can only pair one Bluetooth audio device at a time.
  - You can't use Bluetooth devices and the Wi-Fi Speaker Surround Setup feature (also called Surround) or TV SoundConnect simultaneously.

If you continue to have issues, please call us so we can further assist you with your specific device. Contact us at 1-800-SAMSUNG, 8 AM - 12 AM EST, seven days a week. Our LiveChat agents are also available by clicking on the ‘Support’ link on our website.

~ Samsung Advisor



"}]
reviews.topPositiveReview.reviewText:
Its pretty decent entre 4K TV. Its still a bit on the expensive side but its still better than some of the cheaper competition. I also bought a TCL S546 50" to compare side by side and even tho they both had their pros and cons I preferred and so did my father the image of the AU8000 better so we decided to keep it and return the TCL S546.

Image quality on this TV is clear, vivid but doesn't get very bright. This TV should honestly be $50 less but overall 4/5 Next Upgrade in a couple of years will be one of those higher end models!

Problem is mine came with a dead spot on the screen so I am going to return it and order the same model again because its really good TV.
I attached a picture of the dead spot below.

Thanks

shortDescription: SAMSUNG 50" Class 4K Crystal UHD (2160P) LED Smart TV with HDR UN50TU7000 - Get enhanced smart capabilities with the TU7000. Crystal Processor 4K automatically upscales your favorite movies, TV shows and sports events to 4K. Smart TV powered by Tizen lets you find content and navigate streaming services easily. PurColor fine tunes colors while HDR steps up to millions of shades of color that go beyond what HDTV can offer. And Direct Lit backlighting technology sharpens visuals and improves clarity.
name: SAMSUNG 50" Class 4K Crystal UHD (2160P) LED Smart TV with HDR UN50TU7000B

shortDescription: Experience Quantum Dot technology in our newest premium TV. Our new QLED panel leaps beyond the standard LED screen by adding a quantum filter that precisely controls color output, giving you more vibrant colors, deeper blacks and brighter images than ever before. QLED's sharp contrast and upscaling abilities are hallmarks of the step-up from regular LED, granting your 4K and HDR content extra punch and clarity. With 120hz effective refresh rate, you'll experience sharp images while watching sports, or any fast-moving action for smooth on-screen motion. We've also added Dolby Vision® and Dolby Atmos® technologies to give you the most remarkable, immersive experience possible. Dolby Vision HDR maximizes QLED's display potential for a more lifelike and ultravivid picture, while Dolby Atmos introduces audio that surrounds and moves all around you with breathtaking realism. Plus, local dimming creates intense blacks and stunning contrasts with multiple LED zones. Never miss a detail, even in the darkest of scenes.What about that content, you ask? We've partnered with industry-leading Roku to bring you some of the best shows, movies, media and music available. You'll have thousands of channels to choose from, conveniently presented through your own customizable home screen. Watch via cable, satellite, HDTV antenna or just start streaming from your favorite app. Control your entertainment or even change channels with the Roku voice remote. We'll handle all the software updates as well, automatically, so all you have to worry about is what to watch. Lose yourself in the ultimate viewing experience. Watch onn.™We're onn. to something here. We took the hassle out of buying electronics and built a brand that's fresh and simple. With delightful pops of color, finding the right product has never been easier. Say goodbye to stressful decision-making and fear of the electronics aisle. Our mission is simple… to deliver great products and make it easy. Choose onn. and get back to using your brainpower for the important things in life… like pondering the question, "What should I binge watch this weekend?"
name: onn. 50” QLED 4K UHD (2160p) Roku Smart TV with Dolby Atmos, Dolby Vision, Local Dimming, 120hz Effective Refresh Rate, and HDR (100071700)

shortDescription: SAMSUNG 55" Class 4K Crystal UHD (2160P) LED Smart TV with HDR UN55TU7000 - Get enhanced smart capabilities with the TU7000. Crystal Processor 4K automatically upscales your favorite movies, TV shows and sports events to 4K. Smart TV powered by Tizen lets you find content and navigate streaming services easily. PurColor fine tunes colors while HDR steps up to millions of shades of color that go beyond what HDTV can offer. And Direct Lit backlighting technology sharpens visuals and improves clarity.
name: SAMSUNG 55" Class 4K Crystal UHD (2160P) LED Smart TV with HDR UN55TU7000

Sometimes when it does turn on, you get the title screen saying "Smart TV - Power by Tizen" but wont get any further.', 'reviewTitle': 'Terrible.', 'negativeFeedback': 0, 'positiveFeedback': 0, 'userNickname': 'Roberto', 'photos': [{'caption': None, 'id': 'afd09da6-9403-4432-af64-893f1404e029', 'sizes': {'normal': {'id': 'normal', 'url': 'https://i5.walmartimages.com/dfw/6e29e393-5c23/k2-_cfc108eb-277d-4e99-846d-138a63ff8e68.v1.bin'}, 'thumbnail': {'id': 'thumbnail', 'url': 'https://i5.walmartimages.com/dfw/6e29e393-5c23/k2-_cfc108eb-277d-4e99-846d-138a63ff8e68.v1.bin?odnWidth=150&odnHeight=150&odnBg=ffffff'}}}], 'badges': [{'badgeType': 'Custom', 'id': 'VerifiedPurchaser', 'contentType': 'REVIEW', 'glassBadge': {'id': 'VerifiedPurchaser', 'text': 'Verified Purchaser'}}], 'clientResponses': [{'date': None, 'department': None, 'logoImage': 'https://s3.amazonaws.com/stratos-logos/logos/Samsung.png', 'name': None, 'response': ' Hey Roberto,

We are sorry to hear about your TU7000 TV screen going black. Samsung prides itself on high-quality products and a great customer experience. Please know we are here to help you.

If your TV has a black screen even when it's on, please try these troubleshooting steps for your blank screen issue:

1. Press the Home button on the remote.

If the menu appears, the TV is powered on but is either not on the correct source or not receiving a signal. If the menu does not appear, the TV may have power issues.

Check the red standby light, a little red light at the edge of the TV that you aim the remote at. In everyday use, the red standby light is on when the TV is off (indicating the TV is on standby), and the red standby light is off when the TV is in use (or doesn't have power).

2. Confirm the TV is set to the same source as the external device.

For instance, if your cable box is connected to HDMI 1, set the TV source to HDMI 1.
If the TV is set to the correct source but there is still no image, unplug and reconnect the AV connections one cable at a time from both ends of each cable. If there's any damage to the cable, it will need to be replaced.

After reconnecting the external device, please turn it off and back on.

3. Test the HDMI cable.

Some TVs have an HDMI cable test. Some models only have this test after a software update, and older models do not have it. If your model does not have this test or is not connected by HDMI, skip to the next step.

The test is designed for HDMI cords less than 6 feet long and may not give accurate results on long cords.

To perform the test, make sure the TV's source is still on the HDMI setting for the cable you want to test, and then navigate to Settings > Support > Self Diagnosis > Signal Information > HDMI Cable Test > Start Test.

If the test says, the cable is bad, replace the cable. Service is not required.

4. Test different external devices.

The final thing to rule out is the external device you're using. Try connecting to a different device or using a different source port. If you could not test the cable in the previous step, try swapping the cable, too.

If the TV can display a picture in any other setup, then you've ruled the TV out as the cause of the issue. Keep trying various setups until you identify the device or cable that is not working and troubleshoot or replace it.

The TV will need service if the issue persists after these steps. Please get in touch with us so that we can better investigate your issue and assist you towards a solution or replacement. Please call us at 1-800-SAMSUNG, 8 AM - 12 AM EST, seven days a week. Our LiveChat agents are also available by clicking on the 'Support' link on our website.

~ Samsung Advisor '}], 'syndicationSource': None}, {'reviewId': '253006320', 'rating': 1, 'reviewSubmissionTime': '2/15/2021', 'reviewText': "Purchased this tv a couple of weeks ago (February 2). I've ordered this exact same TV three times.  The first two artived with cracked screens and the third one has a dead spot as shown in the pic.

Not sure if these issues are due to horrible shipping or a bad batch of TVs Wal-Mart is dumping at a reasonable price. 

I will never buy another TV from Wal-Mart but I'm over packing and shipping bad units. I'll see if they will give a partial refund and provide an update of possible. 

Bummed, again....
reviews.topPositiveReview.reviewText: The TV came perfectly wrapped  with no scratches or damages. After mounting, very little to no adjustments were needed. It seems to auto adjust picture quality. It was noticed that there are sound differentials between stations/pictures and the sound has to be adjusted up or down. Especially while viewing streaming apps. Unlike the 55 inch. Not sure why that is. Other than that, enjoying the TV quality.

shortDescription: SAMSUNG 55" Class 4K Crystal UHD (2160P) LED Smart TV with HDR UN55TU7000 - Get enhanced smart capabilities with the TU7000. Crystal Processor 4K automatically upscales your favorite movies, TV shows and sports events to 4K. Smart TV powered by Tizen lets you find content and navigate streaming services easily. PurColor fine tunes colors while HDR steps up to millions of shades of color that go beyond what HDTV can offer. And Direct Lit backlighting technology sharpens visuals and improves clarity.
name: SAMSUNG 55" Class 4K Crystal UHD (2160P) LED Smart TV with HDR UN55TU7000B

Thank you for purchasing the Samsung TU7000 TV and for sharing your experience with your TV not displaying properly. You may want to try the following troubleshooting steps:

1. If any external devices are connected, check all input cable connections

2. If the issue persists, define exactly what is wrong with the display. For example, mosaics and blocks, multiple lines or white dots, and fixed horizontal or vertical lines.

3. Try changing channels using the remote control. Is the issue the same on all channels?

4. Press the Home button (which looks like a house), select Source, and choose another input source. Is the issue the same on all sources?

[{'date': None, 'department': None, 'logoImage': 'https://s3.amazonaws.com/stratos-logos/logos/Samsung.png', 'name': None, 'response': '\nHi Kimberley,

Thank you for purchasing the Samsung TU7000 TV and for sharing your experience with your TV not displaying properly. You may want to try the following troubleshooting steps:

1. If any external devices are connected, check all input cable connections

2. If the issue persists, define exactly what is wrong with the display. For example, mosaics and blocks, multiple lines or white dots, and fixed horizontal or vertical lines.

3. Try changing channels using the remote control. Is the issue the same on all channels?

4. Press the Home button (which looks like a house), select Source, and choose another input source. Is the issue the same on all sources?

5. If the same problem persists, run a diagnostic test. (Home > Settings > Support > Device Care > Self Diagnosis > Picture Test).

6. If the problem disappears during the test, check your TV signal (Home > Settings > Support > Device Care > Self Diagnosis > Signal Information) to check the signal strength. The signal strength must be more than 20 dB (more than 4 bars on the icon) for stable signal reception.

Also, please know we back this Samsung TV with a 1-year limited manufacturer's warranty, including authorized repair for manufacturer defects, if purchased brand-new directly from an authorized seller.

Should your issue persist, please contact Samsung Customer Support. Just call us at 1-800-SAMSUNG, 8 AM - 12 AM EST, seven days a week. Or visit us on the Samsung website and click on the ‘Support’ link for:
1) LiveChat with an agent
2) Manuals, Software, & Warranty Info

~ Samsung Advisor\n '}]
reviews.topPositiveReview.reviewText:
Fantastic TV and price! This was a replacement Samsung TV for my previous 2013 Samsung TV! The old one still works and was given to a neighbor who needed a bigger tv. I paid over $1000 for old one. 
   Extremely easy to set up and use with my cable box. This tv can also be used without cable and has an added feature of Samsung TV Plus, with plenty of shows and movies at no cost to you! Great apps and easy setup for Netflix, Amazon Prime and many more streaming channels! A

shortDescription: The TCL 4-Series Roku TV offers stunning 4K picture quality with four times the resolution of Full HD for enhanced clarity and detail, as well as endless entertainment with thousands of streaming channels. High dynamic range (HDR) technology delivers bright and accurate colors for a lifelike viewing experience. In addition, your favorite HD shows, movies, and sporting events are enhanced to near Ultra HD resolution with 4K Upscaling. Your favorite broadcast TV, streaming channels, gaming console and other devices are front-and-center within a simple, customizable home screen. There’s no more flipping through inputs or wading through complicated menus. The super-simple remote—with about half the number of buttons on a traditional TV remote—puts you in control of your favorite entertainment and includes one-touch shortcuts to popular channels like Netflix.
name: TCL 65" Class 4-Series 4K UHD HDR Smart Roku TV - 65S451

reviews.topNegativeReview.reviewText: Piece of Junk! So flimsy that when I went behind my TV my leg barley touch it and knocked it over and busted my 1 month old TV. The legs are made of a cheap plastic and definitely not strong enough to hold up a 65 inch TV! It broke the plastic screen and now all you can see on the screen is lights and cracked lines all through the screen. I am so upset. I'm going to call the company and see if they will do right and refund me for this poor quality of a tv.
reviews.topNegativeReview.reviewTitle: Flimsy piece of Junk for a TV`

reviews.topPositiveReview.reviewText: Although the volume needs to be higher I did find that if you go into settings. It fixes that. Anyways. I ordered a 58in tv was a hiSense brand tv and after getting it mounted and turned on the screen was broke. So much for fed ex delivery. But I was able to get it refunded and I took the gift card and went for the TCL 65” smart Roku tv. Got it all set up and have been happy ever since. Now. Let see if it lasts long. Lol keeping fingers crossed but I do have to say. TCL is turning into a quality brand now.  I love the picture!!!
reviews.topPositiveReview.reviewTitle: Forget HiSense tvs. TCL is way to go!!

shortDescription: Experience Quantum Dot technology in our newest premium TV. Our new QLED panel leaps beyond the standard LED screen by adding a quantum filter that precisely controls color output, giving you more vibrant colors, deeper blacks and brighter images than ever before. QLED's sharp contrast and upscaling abilities are hallmarks of the step-up from regular LED, granting your 4K and HDR content extra punch and clarity. With 120hz effective refresh rate, you'll experience sharp images while watching sports, or any fast-moving action for smooth on-screen motion. We've also added Dolby Vision® and Dolby Atmos® technologies to give you the most remarkable, immersive experience possible. Dolby Vision HDR maximizes QLED's display potential for a more lifelike and ultravivid picture, while Dolby Atmos introduces audio that surrounds and moves all around you with breathtaking realism. Plus, local dimming creates intense blacks and stunning contrasts with multiple LED zones. Never miss a detail, even in the darkest of scenes.What about that content, you ask? We've partnered with industry-leading Roku to bring you some of the best shows, movies, media and music available. You'll have thousands of channels to choose from, conveniently presented through your own customizable home screen. Watch via cable, satellite, HDTV antenna or just start streaming from your favorite app. Control your entertainment or even change channels with the Roku voice remote. We'll handle all the software updates as well, automatically, so all you have to worry about is what to watch. Lose yourself in the ultimate viewing experience. Watch onn.™We're onn. to something here. We took the hassle out of buying electronics and built a brand that's fresh and simple. With delightful pops of color, finding the right product has never been easier. Say goodbye to stressful decision-making and fear of the electronics aisle. Our mission is simple… to deliver great products and make it easy. Choose onn. and get back to using your brainpower for the important things in life… like pondering the question, "What should I binge watch this weekend?"
name: onn. 65” QLED 4K UHD (2160p) Roku Smart TV with Dolby Atmos, Dolby Vision, Local Dimming, 120hz Effective Refresh Rate, and HDR (100071705)

shortDescription: Escape into awesome entertainment with the VIZIO V-Series 4K UHD Smart TV. With epic 4K UHD picture quality,  Dolby Vision Bright Mode, HDR10, a full array backlight, and active pixel tuning, V-Series provides crystal-clear and sharp picture quality. The next-gen speed and power of the VIZIO IQ Active processor brings astonishing detail and vibrancy to your viewing experience.   Take your gaming to a whole new level with the V-Gaming engine which enables sub 10ms input lag, 4K 48-60 fps Variable Refresh Rate, Auto Game Mode, and a newly added gaming menu. Stream it all with the award-winning SmartCast platform loaded with the best selection of built-in apps including WatchFree+ that lets you enjoy free access to live TV and hundreds of free channels right out of the box. Pair your favorite Bluetooth headphones and hear every word – uninterrupted. SmartCast also works with Apple AirPlay 2 and Chromecast built-in, offering unparalleled entertainment in a size that fits your lifestyle. V-series is everything you need and more in a Smart TV delivering a standout experience at an unmatched price.
name: VIZIO 58" Class V-Series 4K UHD LED Smart TV V585-J01

shortDescription: The Quantum series brings you top of the line quality and all best features you can ask for in a TV. With a pristine and exquisite QLED Panel you have the best quality picture under your roof. Experience quantum color, a realistic image that brings each scene to life with a wider range of colors and dynamic contrast. With Roku Smart TV options you can navigate and stream all of your favorite shows and movies.
name: JVC 50" Class 4K UHD QLED Roku Smart TV Quantum Series

reviews.topPositiveReview.reviewText: got the 50" for less than $250 on sale. glad i did because now its sold out...excellent value. sound and picture are pretty good. will probably not buy a soundbar. I like it the way it is and i use it for gaming. airplay is easy, easy to Bluetooth connect your labtop too. makes you wonder why Samsung TVs are so expensive. i have 2 Samsung tvs and they both needed repair within a year. whatever you do, stay away from Samsung. by the way the tv is light. i mounted it to the wall by myself

shortDescription: The 4-Series Roku TV delivers stunning 4K picture quality with four times the resolution of Full HD for enhanced clarity and detail, as well as endless entertainment with thousands of streaming channels. High dynamic range (HDR) technology delivers bright and accurate colors for a lifelike viewing experience. In addition, your favorite HD shows, movies, and sporting events are upscaled to near Ultra HD resolution with 4K Upscaling. The simple, personalized home screen allows seamless access to thousands of streaming channels, plus your cable box, Blu-ray player, gaming console, and other devices without flipping through inputs or complicated menus. The super-simple remote—with about half the number of buttons on a traditional TV remote—puts you in control of your favorite entertainment.
name: TCL 50" Class 4-Series 4K UHD HDR Roku Smart TV – 50S435

reviews.topNegativeReview.reviewText: Black screen in just 7 months due to bad software update from TCL. Still no resolution or fix provided. Don't buy this product due to low price. Its a piece of crap. If you are thinking of extended warranty from Walmart via Allstate then loss will increase more as Allstate not going to give back anything.

reviews.topPositiveReview.reviewText: We haven't had this one long, but we took a chance about 4 years ago after being lifelong Sony buyers. That one has been exceptional, so hope we find this to be the same.

shortDescription: SAMSUNG 58" Class 4K Crystal UHD (2160P) LED Smart TV with HDR UN58TU7000 2020 - Get enhanced smart capabilities with the TU7000. Crystal Processor 4K automatically upscales your favorite movies, TV shows and sports events to 4K. Smart TV powered by Tizen lets you find content and navigate streaming services easily. PurColor fine tunes colors while HDR steps up to millions of shades of color that go beyond what HDTV can offer. And Direct Lit backlighting technology sharpens visuals and improves clarity.
name: SAMSUNG 58" Class 4K Crystal UHD (2160P) LED Smart TV with HDR UN58TU7000

We are sorry to hear about your TU7000 TV screen going black. Samsung prides itself on high-quality products and a great customer experience. Please know we are here to help you.

If your TV has a black screen even when it's on, please try these troubleshooting steps for your blank screen issue:

1. Press the Home button on the remote.

If the menu appears, the TV is powered on but is either not on the correct source or not receiving a signal. If the menu does not appear, the TV may have power issues.

Check the red standby light, a little red light at the edge of the TV that you aim the remote at. In everyday use, the red standby light is on when the TV is off (indicating the TV is on standby), and the red standby light is off when the TV is in use (or doesn't have power).

2. Confirm the TV is set to the same source as the external device.

For instance, if your cable box is connected to HDMI 1, set the TV source to HDMI 1.
If the TV is set to the correct source but there is still no image, unplug and reconnect the AV connections one cable at a time from both ends of each cable. If there's any damage to the cable, it will need to be replaced.

After reconnecting the external device, please turn it off and back on.

3. Test the HDMI cable.

Some TVs have an HDMI cable test. Some models only have this test after a software update, and older models do not have it. If your model does not have this test or is not connected by HDMI, skip to the next step.

The test is designed for HDMI cords less than 6 feet long and may not give accurate results on long cords.

To perform the test, make sure the TV's source is still on the HDMI setting for the cable you want to test, and then navigate to Settings > Support > Self Diagnosis > Signal Information > HDMI Cable Test > Start Test.

If the test says, the cable is bad, replace the cable. Service is not required.

4. Test different external devices.

The final thing to rule out is the external device you're using. Try connecting to a different device or using a different source port. If you could not test the cable in the previous step, try swapping the cable, too.

If the TV can display a picture in any other setup, then you've ruled the TV out as the cause of the issue. Keep trying various setups until you identify the device or cable that is not working and troubleshoot or replace it.

The TV will need service if the issue persists after these steps. Please get in touch with us so that we can better investigate your issue and assist you towards a solution or replacement. Please call us at 1-800-SAMSUNG, 8 AM - 12 AM EST, seven days a week. Our LiveChat agents are also available by clicking on the 'Support' link on our website.

~ Samsung Advisor '}], 'syndicationSource': None}, {'reviewId': '253006320', 'rating': 1, 'reviewSubmissionTime': '2/15/2021', 'reviewText': "Purchased this tv a couple of weeks ago (February 2). Brought it home, set the tv up picture was working fine. Now I'm getting sound but NO picture. Not happy at all! reviews.topNegativeReview.reviewText:
I've ordered this exact same TV three times.  The first two artived with cracked screens and the third one has a dead spot as shown in the pic.

Not sure if these issues are due to horrible shipping or a bad batch of TVs Wal-Mart is dumping at a reasonable price. 

I will never buy another TV from Wal-Mart but I'm over packing and shipping bad units. I'll see if they will give a partial refund and provide an update of possible. 

Bummed, again....
reviews.topPositiveReview.reviewText: The TV came perfectly wrapped  with no scratches or damages. After mounting, very little to no adjustments were needed. It seems to auto adjust picture quality. It was noticed that there are sound differentials between stations/pictures and the sound has to be adjusted up or down. Especially while viewing streaming apps. Unlike the 55 inch. Not sure why that is. Other than that, enjoying the TV quality.

shortDescription: TCL’s 5-Series QLED TV marries premium picture and endless entertainment for a stellar home theater experience. Quantum Dot technology and the HDR Pro Pack with Dolby Vision combine for greater brightness and contrast, as well as a full palette of rich colors. TCL’s Contrast Control Zone technology optimizes the image across individual zones to yield striking contrast between light and dark areas. The 5-Series models’ AiPQ Engine uses machine-learning algorithms to optimize color, contrast and clarity for an unrivaled 4K HDR experience. Easy Voice Control lets you control your entertainment using just your voice. You’ll be ready to play with Auto Game Mode which adjusts picture settings for an optimized fast-response gaming experience. Plus, the Roku OS provides seamless access to your cable box, Blu-ray player, gaming console
name: TCL 55" Class 5-Series 4K UHD QLED Dolby Vision HDR Roku Smart TV - 55S531

reviews.topNegativeReview.reviewText: The TV was shipped via FedEx. FedEx did not deliver the TV on time. FedEx called me and stated "the driver tried to deliver the package 3 times." I was forced to pick the TV up from FedEx in the rain. Which is not true, I work from home.  I was forced to pick the TV up from FedEx in the rain.The box is in terrible condition. The glass is not centered in the TV frame. You can see light coming out of the front right side of the TV.
reviews.topNegativeReview.reviewTitle: Buying A TV Shipped From Walmart Is A Poor Idea
reviews.topPositiveReview.reviewText: Tv is super easy to setup, and has cable routing that is hidden in each side of the mounting feet. Resolution is perfect, and as described.

shortDescription: The 55in. U6H series ULED TV expands on picture quality and audio upgrades and makes the transition to the Google Tv operating system. The U6H series adds HDR10+ Adaptive and Dolby Vision IQ to its already long list of supported HDR formats. These technologies incorporate environment lighting considerations to their HDR interpretations making HDR more accurate given how dark or bright the lighting within the room. Game Mode gets an upgrade to Game Mode Plus and adds variable refresh rate at 60Hz for smoother gaming on next-generation game consoles. With Wisa-ready software, the U6H is now equipped to connect to the latest Wisa-compatible speakers for a complete surround sound experience without the need for running speaker wire throughout the room. Creating even more robust audio and visual experiences without price-gouging the consumer, the 2022 U6 series continues to be the Hisense television that’s great for everyone. The entertainment you love. With a little help from Google. Google TV brings together movies, shows, live TV and more from across your apps and subscriptions and organizes them just for you. Discover new things to watch with recommendations based on what you watch and what interests you, from across your subscriptions and content available to you. Ask Google to find movies and shows, answer questions, control smart home devices, and more, with your voice. And with the Google TV app you can watch anywhere, anytime.
name: Hisense 55in. Class U6H Series Quantum ULED 4K Smart Google Television

Don't even think about sports, they are a blurry mess.

reviews.topPositiveReview.reviewText: This is my first Google TV and also have Roku.  It is a fairly easy learning process.  Nice picture and easy to set up.  I have only had it a few days, so I cannot give comments as to its reliability.  I got the 55inch Hisense and it is my second Hisense.  So far so good and a good value for the price.

shortDescription: SAMSUNG 60" Class 4K Crystal UHD (2160p) LED Smart TV with HDR UN60TU7000 - Get enhanced smart capabilities with the TU7000. Crystal Processor 4K automatically upscales your favorite movies, TV shows and sports events to 4K. Smart TV powered by Tizen lets you find content and navigate streaming services easily. PurColor fine tunes colors while HDR steps up to millions of shades of color that go beyond what HDTV can offer. And Direct Lit backlighting technology sharpens visuals and improves clarity.
name: SAMSUNG 60" Class 4K Crystal UHD (2160p) LED Smart TV with HDR UN60TU7000

shortDescription: Step up to the AU8000B with upgraded color and 4K essentials. Dynamic Crystal Color injects each scene with millions of vibrant shades of color, while Crystal Processor 4K with UHD Upscaling elevates all your favorite movies, games and shows to gorgeous 4K quality. Smart TV with Multiple Voice Assistants allows you to use your voice to change channels, adjust the volume, or find quickly find content. Plus 3 HDMI inputs provide plenty of connection options.
name: SAMSUNG 50" Class 4K Crystal UHD (2160P) LED Smart TV with HDR UN50AU8000B

I have called Walmart and they are still waiting for the delivery service to process the return to send us our replacement.  I paid well over 1,000 for this product and can't get a resolution in a timely manner and have followed all the requirements for the process.  NOT HAPPY AT ALL,  THIS IS REDICULOUS can't say that I would recommend them.

We insisted on 4K Ultra High Definition for this 70” LED TV, bringing out more lifelike color, texture and detail than ever before. We also partnered with Roku to bring you the best possible content with thousands of channels to choose from, conveniently presented through your own customizable home screen. Watch via cable, satellite, HDTV antenna or just start streaming from your favorite app. Like the sound of your own voice You can actually use it with the Roku mobile app to search for a title, artist, actor or director, or just go old-school with our handy remote. We handle all software updates too, automatically, so all you have to worry about is what to watch. Lose yourself in the ultimate viewing experience. Watch on with our onn. 4K UHD 70" Smart TV. We're onn. to something here. We took the hassle out of buying electronics and built a brand that's fresh and simple. With delightful pops of color, finding the right product has never been easier. Say goodbye to stressful decision-making and fear of the electronics aisle. Our mission is simple… to deliver great products and make it easy. Choose onn. and get back to using your brainpower for the important things in life like pondering the question, "What should I binge watch this weekend?"

So finally we turned on the TV and wow!! I am impressed!! The colors a vibrant and crisp especially with 4k. It was not pix-elated as I initially thought it would be. Setup was pretty fast. LOVE LOVE THIS TV!!!', 'reviewTitle': 'My new favorite!', 'negativeFeedback': 62, 'positiveFeedback': 105, 'userNickname': 'Krissy', 'photos': [{'caption': None, 'id': '90fde199-3eff-41e4-a439-343167c4f736', 'sizes': {'normal': {'id': 'normal', 'url': 'https://i5.walmartimages.com/dfw/6e29e393-b621/k2-_1cc8ccca-36eb-45f3-9bae-b90d51222139.v1.jpg'}, 'thumbnail': {'id': 'thumbnail', 'url': 'https://i5.walmartimages.com/dfw/6e29e393-b621/k2-_1cc8ccca-36eb-45f3-9bae-b90d51222139.v1.jpg?odnWidth=150&odnHeight=150&odnBg=ffffff'}}}, {'caption': None, 'id': 'c4ee9637-4ce3-4934-95b1-2d682a978918', 'sizes': {'normal': {'id': 'normal', 'url': 'https://i5.walmartimages.com/dfw/6e29e393-25ea/k2-_58d70d59-e8b1-43e7-8b51-1dbb371791ce.v1.jpg'}, 'thumbnail': {'id': 'thumbnail', 'url': 'https://i5.walmartimages.com/dfw/6e29e393-25ea/k2-_58d70d59-e8b1-43e7-8b51-1dbb371791ce.v1.jpg?odnWidth=150&odnHeight=150&odnBg=ffffff'}}}], 'badges': [{'badgeType': 'Custom', 'id': 'IncentivizedReviewYes', 'contentType': 'REVIEW', 'glassBadge': {'id': 'IncentivizedReview', 'text': 'Incentivized Review'}}], 'clientResponses': None, 'syndicationSource': None}, {'reviewId': '235709154', 'rating': 4, 'reviewSubmissionTime': '8/16/2020', 'reviewText': 'It is remarkable how affordable big UHD 4K TVs have become. This Onn 70" UHD Roku TV is not only budget friendly and smart but with some tweaking, it is also a solid performer. It is not top tier by any means but it is still a major upgrade over the secondary 32" TV in our playroom. 

A big TV can deliver an immersive viewing experience and this Onn 70" TV is big. It measured 62 inches wide and if you intend to use the stand, just know that the legs are also 62 inches apart. I chose to hang this TV on the wall instead and it was a bit of a hassle as the standard VESA holes on the back were too close to the bottom which gave me very little wiggle room to align the brackets. Also the fixed and low profile TV mount I used presented another issue as the TV hugged the wall a bit too closely which made it hard to see and connect cables to the recessed video and audio ports. 

Setting up the TV for viewing did not take long and technically you do not need an Internet connection, but you will want to have it to setup Roku, get over-the-air updates and take advantage of all the features this smart TV has to offer. The TV came with an integrated network port, Wi-Fi and the Roku platform to provide easy access to hundreds of free and paid streaming channels. Using Roku is free but you will need to create an account and link the TV to it. As part of creating an account, Roku will ask for a credit card or PayPal account to make it easy to pay for any future subscriptions or rentals. If you are not ready to provide a payment method to keep on file just search online for how to bypass that step.

The baked-in Roku made this TV the easiest TV I have ever operated. The remote control is so simple with very few buttons but some how provided all the functionalities that I needed. I especially like how the * (asterisk) button quickly brought up a transparent panel for adjusting image and audio settings and that was a good thing because this TV did not look its best out of the box and needed some tweaking. The screen did not have perfect black uniformity or intense colors but after adjusting various video and audio settings, I was very happy with the end results. So far the settings that worked for me are backlight=60, dynamic contrast=OFF, contrast=50 for movies or 70 for games, sharpness=30, sound=theater and volume=leveling. 

I must add a disclaimer that the bias lighting behind the TV in my shared images did not come with the TV. I bought that sticky strip of LED light separately. A 16 foot strip is the perfect length to go around the back of this 70" TV. Bias lighting not only looks cool but it also reduces eye strain and improves the quality of your nighttime viewing.

Lastly, there are some extra features that are worth mentioning. HDR10 is included for better contrast and richer colors. I can confirm that the feature was recognized by the XBox One console for games and Blu-ray movies. This TV also supports wireless screen mirroring (over the same Wi-Fi network) from a Windows 10 computer or a newer Android phone for a quick presentation or for showing off vacation photos.

It is understandable to have certain preconceptions against this inexpensive and lesser known brand especially regarding the TV's longevity. Fortunately, Onn offers a two year warranty with registration and after I spent some time with this TV, I can say that the TV is a solid choice as a secondary TV or if you are on a tight budget.', shortDescription: Sure, the Hisense 55 inch U7G TV Smart TV series is great for Netflix, the big game, and the real housewives of wherever. But the U7G is made for the gamers. It's got our exclusive ULED technologies, 4K resolution, Quantum Dot Color, Dolby Vision HDR, Full Array Local Dimming zones and Android TV operating system. On top of all that, Hisense added a 120Hz Native panel for smoother, more fluid motion and HDMI 2.1, Variable Refresh Rate and Auto Low Latency Mode for gaming that looks sick, even if you suck. The U7G also has up to 1,000 nits peak brightness, which makes HDR ?pop? and means the picture is lit no matter how bright the room. All this looks great on paper. Now think how much better it would look on this TV.
name: Restored Hisense ULED Premium 55 Inch Quantum Dot QLED Series Android 4K Smart TV (55U7G) (Refurbished)

shortDescription: The 4-Series Roku TV delivers stunning 4K picture quality with four times the resolution of Full HD for enhanced clarity and detail, as well as endless entertainment with thousands of streaming channels. High dynamic range (HDR) technology delivers bright and accurate colors for a lifelike viewing experience. In addition, your favorite HD shows, movies, and sporting events are upscaled to near Ultra HD resolution with 4K Upscaling. The simple, personalized home screen allows seamless access to thousands of streaming channels, plus your cable box, Blu-ray player, gaming console, and other devices without flipping through inputs or complicated menus. The super-simple remote with about half the number of buttons on a traditional TV remote puts you in control of your favorite entertainment.
name: TCL 43" Class 4-Series 4K UHD HDR Roku Smart TV - 43S435
